animal.description:
Sophie is a sophisticated girl who enjoys the finer things in life; like car rides around the city and napping on fluffy blankets. Sophie is about four years old and found in a shelter. She was optimistic at first, smiling in all her photos and played nicely in play groups - however, the longer she was at the shelter, the more depressed she became. When rescue found her, she stopped smiling and had gained weight from laying around eating her feelings (dog biscuits). Sophie immediately bounced back to her sparkling smiling self when she met her foster mom and moved into her downtown apartment life. Sophie has thrived as an urban dog; leash trained and friendly with all people. She is just as happy watching life from the balcony as she is, walking along the streets. Sophies favorite thing is cuddling - second is dessert time! (...Sophie last weighted in at 80 lbs so she is strong and pulls a little when exctied) 

Sophie likes other dogs and plays briefly with dogs she's met. She mostly sniffs then ignores them. Sophie loves kids and gives gentle kisses, not jumping or knocking into them. Sophie is good for movies on the couch or brunch dates downtown. If you are seeking a stylish, sophisticated lady to join your life - this is your new bestie! Curvy is beautiful and Sophie would prefer to maintain her figure as is (girl can eat!). Sophie's ideal family would get her a bling collar and proudly show off this social, gentle and gorgeous blue American Pitbull Terrier.

She is up to date on vaccines according to her age, she has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer. She is microchipped, spayed, comes with 6 months of preventatives, one month free trial of pet insurance, all of our animals receive a health certificate (this states a licensed veterinary saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, it is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and transport is included in adoption fee ($450.00).

She is currently being fostered in Houston, Tx but will be traveling to the PNW as soon as she finds her perfect home! She's hoping to leave town 02-06-2021 so she can see the snow! 

Please inquire by submitting an application (Application link:) https://petstablished.com/petlover/general_form/30256

Adoption Coordinator: leah@threelittlepittiesrescue.org

Please go to our website to see more about our rescue and what we do! We are very proud of our hard work in saving as many animals as we can, giving them what they need, and matching them with the right families.

Emmitt is a two year old American bulldog mix. He seems to be mixed with a whole lot of love, because Emmitt is nothing but a big lap dog! Emmitt is nervous in a new surrounding at first but warms up to everyone he meets very quickly. He is potty trained so he doesn't need a crate. He loves his foster pups, big and small, and gets along well with his foster kitten. His favorite things to do are go on walks, play with his foster brother, and sit on your lap. He needs to continue his obedience training with his furever home, but he loves training sessions and he catches on very quickly. Emmitt is smart, energetic, loving pup who needs a family who can handle his energy. A fenced yard is a must, and preferably another pup so he can spend his days happily playing. NO Small Children - only older mature children for this guy please!

If you think he may be the right fit for you, visit www.fluffanimalrescue.org and complete an application to begin the adoption process.

animal.description:
This girl is very friendly with people...all people...but not necessarily good with all other dogs. She would be happy as an only dog or with another dog but the dog must be a calm, neutral, well behaved dog. We think she may be Ok with cats since she grew up with them. 

Dolly had been under-exercised and over fed in her prior home, so she was overweight prior but we've got her on a proper diet and getting lots of daily exercise, so she now weighs 80 lbs. 

Here's info from Dolly's trainer on the type of home that would be a good fit for this dog: "Quiet type of household. No young kids. She is just too rough. Kids 10 and older ok, but it really depends on the kids. If they are quiet kids it's fine. If it is kids that wrestle all the time it would be too much. She is wonderful with my 12 year old. She gets along well with dogs, but is still learning proper skills, so if there is a dog it needs to be a calm, neutral, well behaved dog. She will also be happy being the only dog. She needs at least an hour long leash walk every day to keep her mind and body calm." 
 

Dolly needs a home with Rottie-owner/ trainer experienced adopters only. We will not adopt her to anyone who hasn't owned one of her breed prior. She means well, but is young & quite boisterous and not for anyone who is passive. She will need to be trained with a kind but firm owner. 

Dolly is crate trained and house-trained. She's been quite a puller on the leash but with the proper tools, her trainer is working on that. Sadly, she was chained in her prior home which only reinforces pulling behavior on a leash. You'll need to be a strong person to manage her until she is fully trained to walk properly on the leash. We do require that anyone who adopts her will work with our dog trainer/behaviorist from the start. 
 

Pls apply to adopt only if you have Rottie owning/training experience prior and are willing to work with our trainer. 
We will not adopt this dog to you if you don't.

The first step is to fill out our Adoption Application, which doesnt obligate you to adopt but does help us to learn if the home you might offer would be a good fit. 

 

To apply to adopt go to: www.pendletonpawswv.com 

Click on Heading Available for Adoption

Click on link, this takes u to all our adoptable pets

Scroll thru pets to find the pet u want

Click on ADOPT on that pets page 

This is our Adoption Application

Fill it out in its entirety, then click SUBMIT to send it to us.

animal.description:
Please note: We are a small rescue and do not have the resources to respond to inquiries. If a dog is on our website, it is still available. We can not arrange meet & greet without an application.

Adoption fees: $450 for dogs 12 months/younger, $400 for dogs 1-2 Yrs,
$350 for dogs 3-5yrs, and $300 for 6yrs and older

Max joined our pack last week from the Stanislaus Animal Shelter. Max is settling In nicely with his foster mom and dad, Susan and Chris. This is what they had to say about Max.
Max is a very friendly and active German Shepherd. At 7 years old, he has a very sweet personality and would be great with an active family. He loves his walks and has even started running with his foster dad.
He is well behaved indoors (no accidents at all) and doesnt seem interested in chewing shoes or any other items in the house. Max is like a shadow around the house and in the yard, he loves spending time with people.
Chris is working with Max on his leash manners and he has also had the chance to meet some other dogs. Max can get a little exuberant with other dogs, but responds well to direction from his leader and just wants to play.
Max has met some younger kids (maybe 5 years old) and was friendly and well behaved with them. He is not cat tested. Part of the reason Max is so well behaved is that he came from a home environment and only ended up in the shelter because his owner passed away.
Max would flourish in an active household where he could get some daily exercise. He is a friendly, well-balanced dog and will make a great companion to a lucky family.
Max is fully vaccinated and neutered and weighs about 72lbs.

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please review our adoption process and then fill out an online adoption form at https://www.calpaws.org/adopting. Experience with obedience training is definitely preferred. We are a small rescue and do not have the resources to respond to inquiries. If a dog is our website, it is still available. We can not arrange meet & greet without an application.

We are always in need of fosters for the amount of dogs we have coming in. Being a foster is such a rewarding experience. If you are interested please review https://www.calpaws.org/fostering

animal.description:
Do you like long walks? Do you like to spoon when you nap? If so I am the girl for you! My name is Journey. I came to Colorado expecting a litter of puppies. I had 10 healthy babies but they are 8 weeks old now so I am all done being a mom and super happy being a dog. I am a 3 year old pittie and my foster moms say I am such a good girl. I am house broken, know basic commands, and crate trained but I dont need to be crated. I sleep all night in the living room with no accidents and I dont get in to anything! I have no food or toy aggression. I absolutely love people and other dogs. I would be so happy if my forever family has kids and even a furry sibling for me. If you are looking for a girl with a moderate level of energy, enjoys snuggling on the couch, completely trained and lots of life left please consider adopting me.

If you are interested in adopting, please visit our website and complete an adoption application at www.elpasocountycanine.org/available-dogs

animal.description:
Logan is an amazing greyhound weimeraner mix (her sibling Dallas was DNA tested via Embark) with an approximate birthday of 06/30/2019. She is a nervous girl who likely missed out on early social skills that would have helped her function normally in life, but she is joyous and playful and capable of bonding with people if given time. 

Logan will require a family who will never leave her outside unattended and if the household fence is lower than 6' or there is no fence, she will always have to be taken out on leash. Because of her propensity for flight in stressful situations, she will never be suitable for any off leash activities. 

She is fine with cats and absolutely loves other dogs. She would thrive in a multi dog household where the other dogs were confident and balanced. She would make an excellent companion for a dog who recently lost their house mate, and would be suitable with most people, including children as long as everyone could accept her shyness. 

She is likely not completely house trained if given ample freedom in the home, but when kept on a normal routine and crated when not interacting with her people, she makes no bathroom mistakes and hasn't pottied her crate a single time. She is working on her leash walking skills and she is learning to snuggle and eat meals on a regular schedule. She loves her crate and is comfortable in it for a full work day as needed. She is too nervous to benefit from obedience training at this time, so we are sticking with the basics. She is currently able to sleep through about half the night in bed before getting restless and needing to be crated. 

Logan will likely never be a "normal dog", but for a family looking for a loyal and hilarious companion, she would be an excellent choice. She is blossoming and making progress by the day and is a blessing to have around. She comes spayed, vaccinated, microchipped and dewormed. Her adoption fee is $200.00. To apply, visit www.murcismission.org. 

Thank you for checking out our girl!

** WEEKEND APPLICANTS **

We realize that you are excited & anxious to know but calling us daily to check keeps us from working on the applications & delays the process. 

ONLY ONE APPLICATION NEEDED 
If interested in more than one pup just put all the names on one application. If you already have an approved application then just email us at lchsmanager@gmail.com to tell us you which animals you want your approved application applied to.

Only approved applicants wearing a MASK will be allowed to enter our facility and meet our pets. 

Please do not request an appointment if you or anyone in your household have had symptoms of COVID 19 or been around anyone that you know has been positive or experienced symptoms within past 14 days. It is of the utmost importance that our staff stays healthy so our pets can be taken care of. After someone leaves our facility everything is cleaned with bleach water for the safety of all!

All our pets are posted online and we continue to take applications until they are actually adopted. Many times things change and an approved adopter does not adopt the animal so we do maintain a wait list when necessary. 

Thank you for reading this and following the directions. It is a part of our approval process!

animal.description:
Dakota
Breed: Staffordshire Bull Terrier
Gender: Female
Adoption Fee: $175
Dakota is a super friendly girl looking for a loving home to call her own. She will be a great companion for almost any home. This silly girl get the ""wiggle booty"" when she greets new people!!! You will never have a dull or lonely moment with Dakota by your side!!! Please fill out an adoption application today!!!Please read the animal bios completely before requesting additional information as we do our best to answer the most frequently ask questions in these bios. 

In order to adopt one of our animals an application must be submitted and approved. You can find these applications by going to http://humanemorgan.org/index.php?page=adoption 

ABOUT ADOPTING FROM THE HSMC: 
The shelter address is 1170 Fairground Rd. Madison, GA 30650. For more information on any of our pets, please feel free to email us at INFO@HUMANEMORGAN.ORG give us a call at 706-343-9977. 
All dogs are heartworm negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
All cats are FeLv/FIV negative, current on vaccines/dewormings, and microchipped. 
We are open 10am-5pm Monday-Saturday, we schedule our last adoption at 4pm everyday to allow our staff enough time to feed and walk dogs. 
We are an animal shelter and therefore are not able to individually potty train our residents. Many adult dogs do arrive ""house broken"" however due to animal behavior any change in environment will make an emotional impact on the animals and therefore initiate unwanted behaviors during the acclamation period. Please keep this in mind. Puppies do not have the biological maturity to maintain absolute bladder or bowel control and will require a certain degree of potty training and house breaking. Please consider the time and commitment it takes to provide the necessary building blocks for these special babies, prior to submitting your application. 
If you have any questions please email us at info@humanemorgan.org and provide name of the animal you are interested in, in the subject line. 
Thank you, HSMC Staff 

ADOPTION FEES Adoption Fees may change without notice. Always verify the fee when finalizing the adoption. 
~ Cats and Kittens ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $100 
* 1-5 Years = $75 
* Over 5 Years = $50 
** Purebred cats and kittens may be subject to special pricing 

~ Mix Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $200 
* 1 -3 Years = $175 
* 4-8 Years = $150 
* Over 8 Years = $100

~ Purebred and Designer Breed Dogs ~ 
* Under 1 Year = $375 
* 1-3 Years = $350 
* 4-8 Years = $275 
* Over 8 Years = $150 

~ Medical and Special Needs ~ 
We have rescued dogs and cats which require additional medical care or that have special needs which are not life threatening. In these cases we may require a higher fee to help recoup the costs of their care while at our rescue.

animal.description:
***All animals listed on our website are in private foster homes. To arrange a meet and greet with a dog, you MUST fill out the adoption application so that it can be sent to the foster parent for review to determine if your home is a match for the dog. If a dog receives multiple applications, we operate on a best-fit basis, not first come first served.***

Hi I am Tigre, aka T, aka Mr T

I am a 1 1/2 year Boxer mix. I am up to date on all my shots and I get my heartworm prevention on the 5th of each month. Now that we got all that out of the way let me tell you about myself.

My girl being only 18 couldn't take care of me a more, I miss her, she dropped me off with my grand-humans. Their house is fun I have 4 fur-cousins to play with and also a bunch of human cousins to play with. I really do love playing with all of them.

I would love to be a lap pup and snuggle with you on the couch. Oh and there's nothing better than snuggling in bed.
I am house trained and can be left alone although I will get on the couch to sleep if nothing is on it and blocking my way. I do go in my crate to sleep, my bed is very comfy. The door to my crate is always open.

I love my play toys, my rope, tug toy and bones. They are fun to play with.

I love to run and play in the backyard, I have lots of energy but when the time calls for it I am a couch potato. I do need a fenced yard, I have been know to explore the neighborhood from time to time, maybe you can help me with that.

My grand-humans have spoiled me, they do give me table scraps from time to time and I always get dry food mixed with can food and some water added.

I know they are going to miss me a lot but will be so happy for me when I find just the right forever home that is filled with love and treats. I know it will be a little hard for me too, but I will adapt quickly with lots of hugs and love.

My perfect home will be a home with children and I don't even mind a new fur brother or sister. Most of all the home needs loves.
animal.name: Tigre

animal.description:
Hi everyone! My name is Eira (which means snow in Welsh because of my pretty creamy color). I am the most loving girl and love to be close to my people. Surprisingly, I never had a family back in Texas until finding a foster family in Colorado. It's so nice! I love having furry foster siblings to hang out with, comfortable blankets to spread out on, and a yard to run around in. I am learning the ropes very quickly! I can now sit on command and am excited to learn more from my loving humans. My foster mom says that I am the most eager-to-please dog in the world. I will listen to whatever you say and will do my best to be a good girl at all times. All I need is love and some good pets. 

I am athletic, medium-energy, and a small-medium size. I am a good fit for adventures with a little room in their tent or a family who enjoys walks and has room on their couch. I am learning to play fetch with my furry foster sister. I love all dogs that I meet, big and small. Sometimes humans are a little scary if they're in my yard and I don't recognize them immediately, but I warm up pretty quickly! Just have to make sure my humans know there's an intruder first, then I can ask for all the pets once I meet them.

I am the momma to a beautiful litter of puppies, but now that they are growing up, it's time I find a furever family to call my own!

 

 

Adoption fee includes the following:


	Spay/Neuter
	Rabies Vaccination
	Distemper / Parvo Vaccines (includes series of 3 for puppies)
	Bordetella
	Microchip with prepaid lifetime registration
	Deworming

animal.description:
Meet this little stud Puffin!

Hi friends! My name is Puffin and Im one chill little dude! Im an 8-year-old, 6.5-pound, Chihuahua. Even though Im no spring chicken, this Puffin still has a ton of pep him his step! Im a totally healthy fella and Ill make sure to get neutered soon. I was recently rescued from Tijuana with the rest of my Artic pals. We migrated our way up to San Diego and life has been un-burr-leavable, but I cant wait to find myself a find my furever flock!

Im a mellow man that gets along with pretty much everyone under the sun. I like other pooches and even cats! Even though Im friendly, I pretty much just leave other furry creatures alone so that I can give all my attention to my hoomans. I would prefer to be the only boy doggo around. Im the ultimate companion who will give you my whole heart! I love kids too, I just need a gentle introduction.

My favorite place to be is in your lap, but Ill also settle for an elbow, knee, or between your feet. Im an affectionate fella! When Im not being a cuddle bug, Im a pro at fetch. I love tennis balls and chewing on my little squeaky toys too!

Im learning how to be a good boy and have fewer accidents in the house when on a regular walk schedule. Im still working on it, but practice makes pawfect. Im getting better on the leash when Im with other pups because I follow the pack, but when Im alone, Im not quite sure what we are supposed to be doing. Im sure Ill get the hang of it soon!

If youre looking for a superb snuggler who will be your personal shadow, Im the little man for you. Id do well in a home with or without other pets, but no other male dogs please, and would be fine with kids as long as have a proper introduction. Im an easy-going guy who likes to play, but all-in-all, Im pretty low maintenance! So what do you say? Lets meet today! My adoption fee is $200 and that includes spaying/neutering, shots, and microchip. If you want to take me home, please fill out the form on the website here: https://theanimalpad.org/adoption-application/

animal.description: Meet our rescued puppy Ivan.  We rescued the boy Ivan from the streets of Russia, where he was starving, freezing and very afraid. Kennedy airport, a cheerful, active, very gentle and affectionate puppy ran out to meet us.  Ivan is 10 months old.  Ivan is very human-oriented and loves all animals, dogs, cats.  Likes to walk a lot, play with a ball, jump and run.  We are looking for the best family without small children, because Ivan knows how to jump for love.  If you are interested in our Ivan, please send your request to us  by email and we will send you an applications : dsprescue@gmail.com or send the text 347-530-7069.  or 215-264-3704.

animal.description: The only thing this Pirate will steal is your heart! From the moment he jumps in your car, this well-behaved pup will be by your side or keeping you in his sight at all times. When you're working at your desk or in the kitchen, he will always lay close by (or under your chair). He also may sit up and very kindly say 'Hey, it's dinner time'! Pirate is hesitant with new people, but turns into a love bug within a few minutes (especially if you bribe him with treats). This pup is so friendly, and just wants to snuggle all the time. He has calmly hung out with dogs he's seen on walks, just sniffing and nuzzling them. And he's been curious about babies in strollers, but hasn't approached them. Pirate loves carrying his sock monkey from room to room. He would also love to sit on your lap when you're on the floor with him. He has adapted to house-life quite well. When this house-trained boy needs to go out, he just walks to the door and lays down, making a little whining noise if not noticed. In foster, he has slept in his crate every night and is now starting to take naps there during the day, doing well when home alone. He is recovering from a hind leg injury, so he takes medication twice a day and rests in his crate. A smart boy, he responds to his name, 'settle' if he is getting too excited and 'no' and 'lay down'. Pirate would be best suited for adults or families with older children, just because of his size and his desire to be a lap dog. Pirate will be an amazing companion to anyone lucky enough to meet him. Search no further for your treasure, cause this guy is it!

animal.description:
Name: Lilah 
Age: 12 yo 
Weight: 14 lbs 
Sex/Spayed or neutered?: female/spayed   
Coat: wire 
Color: brown
Energy Level: medium 
Adoption Fee: $150
Contact: amanda@myardor.com

Hi there every-pawdy, my name is Lilah and I’m new here to this nice rescue. My previous owner had to go into a nursing home and was unable to take me with her so the RR opened their arms and took me right in to find me another home to spend the rest of my years in. My foster mom doesn’t know anything about my medical history other than I am spayed and my mouth is absolutely horrid.  I am in desperate need for a dental and to get up to date on my vaccines and heartworm test. I also have IVDD so my back and legs are very weak and wobbly. I try to hold my business until I get outside but sometimes can’t. My foster mom is still trying to figure out how extensive my special needs are. We will know more once I am seen by our vets on Thursday (Jan 28). I will need to go to a home that is familiar with Dachshunds with back issues and has lots of patience to help with my potty accidents. I am a super sweet girl, and am very curious about my new surroundings. I follow my foster parents around all over the house, and even get up to a nice little jog out in the yard. Feel free to email my foster mom with any questions you have and she’ll do her best to answer them. I’ll update y’all as soon as I get the all clear from the docs .. Go ahead and send in an application if you think I could make a wonderful addition to your household. Thanks! 

If you want to help with this dog’s medical expenses: 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/how-to-help

If you want to adopt this dog, apply at the link! 
https://therescuedrescuers.org/adoption-application

Spirit is an old soul that's cautious around new people and things but given time, warms up nicely. Once he's comfortable, he loves affection and positive reinforcement. He needs someone with lots of patience as he does best with baby steps. Trying new things slowly, a little at a time. He's getting better on the leash and is very smart. He has nice manners and a quiet sweetness. He will do well working with a professional trainer to build his confidence and a tighter bond with his new family.

This sweet sensitive boy longs to please. He loves gentle head scratches, positive reassurance, chewing on antlers, and training sessions with plenty of treats! He is wary of new people, but with love and patience he will become a faithful friend. He has a gentle soul and learns quickly. Spirit is bonded with Blossom. Blossom's outgoing nature is a great balance as she brings out Spirit's playful side. This bonded pair are the most content and "easy" dogs I've ever met. Spirit is a really good boy!

animal.description:
Animal Profile: Jack is a ~5 year old ~15lb chihuahua/dachshund mix. He was rescued from Fresno, CA after his family could no longer keep him. Once Jack was rescued and joined us, it became clear he never had much exposure outside of his previous home. He was very fearful of people and a leash, but with time, patience, and dedication from his wonderful foster family - he has really flourished into a loving, wonderful companion in their home.

Foster Update:

Jack is looking for a special home that has the patience to work with him through his initial fears and suspicions to get to the sweet, loyal, and loving little boy he is underneath. He likes dogs of all sizes (especially small dogs who will play with him) as well as cats, and is looking for a home with other pets and with one or more humans who can spend a lot of time at home with him. In his foster home, Jack enjoys snuggling on the couch with his foster mom (he's a perfectly-sized lap dog), getting ear scratches and belly rubs, playing with stuffed toys, exploring the outdoors, dutifully following his foster mom around the house while she does chores, and cuddling with his dog and cat foster siblings while his foster mom works in her home office. At night, he prefers to sleep under the covers, usually on his foster mom's feet. He will make a loyal and loving companion for the right person, and will likely be the type of dog who attaches hard to one person in a household. He would enjoy a securely-fenced yard that he can explore with his dog siblings, and will thrive in a committed home that continues to work with him to overcome his fears of new people and new situations.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $475, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Animal History: This dog was rescued from euthanasia at a high-kill shelter in California and will be available for adoption in Seattle, once evaluated in a loving foster home in the greater Seattle area.

animal.description:
*FOSTER OR ADOPTER NEEDED ASAP*

This handsome gentleman is Roscoe!  Roscoe is 8 years-young and his family has to move and sadly, can't take this cutie with them.  Roscoe is now in need of a new home and we’re hoping to help him find just that!

Roscoe is very very spoiled.  He prefers to sleep with someone, which he has done since a puppy, but he does have 2 wonderful comfortable beds that he likes and will use if that is necessary.  He snores when he is in deep sleep.  He also enjoys walks and car rides and he likes to play ball and fetch. 
 
He gives himself a pedicure when his nails get too long.  Roscoe LOVES the water.  He enjoys going swimming in pools and ponds!  He also enjoys digging himself a hole to lay in and sun himself, but he prefers to stay in the a/c!  He loves to lay on a couch and snuggle while humans watch TV, but he doesn't realize he is not a lap dog, since he has always been around small dogs (Chihuahua and Pug).  He is house trained and will always let you know when he needs to go out!
 
He loves kids and is very helpful with the kids, if they cry or do something they are not supposed to be doing he will pace or come nudge your hand!  He has been around kids since they were babies, they are now 11 and 4 and he just loves them, but he does need to be careful, as he doesn't realize he is a big dog.  Although he has gotten along with the little dogs, he is getting older and prefers to be the only dog!
 
He does seem to have some food sensitivity, but adding in a small amount of pumpkin seems to help.  His current diet is Victor Hi performance, which has helped keep his coat shiny!  So if he needs to change his food, it should be done carefully and slowly!

Please help us get Roscoe into a safe, loving forever home!  If you're unable to help by adopting, sharing this post or donating is always appreciated.  Don't forget, Passion for Pitties is a 501(c)(3), so all donations are tax-deductible!…every little bit helps!
 
If you would like to adopt loving Roscoe, please fill out an application at www.passionforpitties.com under the “Adorable Adoptables” heading.

animal.description:
Meet Hazel!
Hazel is a purebred German Shepherd born November 3rd 2016
Hazel was not properly socialized as a young puppy, therefore she will do best in a home with a submissive male of her size or larger or as an only dog. She does enjoying socializing with other dogs but can be skittish when they bark or come at her quickly. Absolutely NO small dogs, cats or small animals in the home.
Hazel has spent months training at Mattox Dog Training and has made a lot of progress with appropriate behavior around humans and canines alike.
Hazel’s new home will require extensive breed knowledge and adults only-NO exceptions
We will require potential adopters to meet with her former trainers and learn the commands Hazel is used to responding to.
Hazel will require an owner committed to ongoing training to ensure she remains a good canine citizen.
Hazel will require a home with a secure 6 ft fenced yard, some exceptions may be made depending on experience with the breed.
Hazel has a cautious nature (as the breed typically does) she will do best in a home that can be understanding of this.Hazel is crate trained though she is 100% trustworthy without the crate while alone in the home.
Hazel loves balls and adores water-except if it’s bath time ?
If you think Hazel is the perfect match for you, applications can be submitted at www.MikeysChance.com 
All large and/or active dogs will require a full fenced (6ft) secure yard. 
No children under 5. 

Like all Mikey's Chance dogs, this dog will come to you from a foster home that has provided loving one-on-one attention, socialization and some basic training, as well as quality food and exercise. 

Applications can be found at www.mikeyschance.com and completed on a computer, tablet, and/or phone. Please note that adopters are not chosen on a first come, first served basis, but full consideration is given to the best fit for the dog AND the adopter. Applications can take up to 3 weeks to process. Application submission DOES NOT guarantee approval for adoption.

animal.description:
Pearl is an absolutely delightful and joyful little girl. She's probably around 13 to 14 years old. Because of a thyroid issue she was a little overweight when she arrived at her foster home. With diet and exercise she is now not only looking great, she is able to run and climb steps. She is easy-going, cuddly and entertaining. She has made herself right at home with her foster's three Chihuahuas. She sleeps in a bed in the office, and there is never a peep out of her during the night. She is house-trained, but on rainy days she chooses to use a puddle pad more often than not. She loves the outdoors and foraging for food under the fruit trees. She is a food thief and will not only eat her food, she will attempt to eat the other dogs' food also. Not really an issue with supervision, but mostly fun and entertaining to watch the action unfold. This has improved over time with guidance. One of the most endearing qualities about Pearl is that when she barks, she throws her head back and her front paws leave the ground. Cute as can be. This little girl will make someone a wonderful companion!

animal.description: Hello, my name is Lady (HWTH#21027A).  I am a Lab mix, born on 10/4/2010 and I weigh approximately 45 lbs.  My mother Diamond (adopted), my brother Mufasa (HWTH#21026A), and I were relinquished together to Halfway to Home after our owner passed away.  We are a little overwhelmed after having being taken from the only home we have ever known, but the people here are very nice and are helping us prepare to find new homes to spend our golden years.  I may be a senior, but I am friendly and I have a lot of life left in me.  I am a little overweight but with properly-portioned good-quality kibble and regular exercise I should easily lose those extra pounds. Senior dogs make wonderful companions because unlike puppies, we don't need a lot of exercise, we are good at entertaining ourselves, we understand the difference between a dog toy and your furniture, and we adjust easily to your schedule so you will get a good night's sleep!  I would be an ideal friend for a retired individual or couple who enjoys going for leisurely walks and having a loyal buddy laying at their feet.  I have been around children, other dogs, and even cats for most of my life so I would be a good fit for most families (little children might be a little much).  My exercise needs are moderate so although a home with fenced yard would be great, I might be ok in a ground-floor apartment or condo as long as I have an outdoor space to do my business and you are willing to take me for a couple of short walks daily.  More than anything else I am looking for a family to love me and that I can love back.  So what do you think?  If you would like more information or would like to make an appointment to meet me, please call Sandy at tele#661-824-4495 (this is a landline).  I'll be waiting for you!

animal.description:
Meet adorable Jade! She and her sister and brother (Juneau) arrived into PetConnect's care a week ago and are thriving in their foster homes. The sweeties are typical playful, loving puppies! They would love a home with another pup to play with, but they'd also be okay as an only dog. They will do well with respectful children. They will need a home with someone around during the day to continue to work with them on their housetraining and socializing. They will also need a home with a private yard where they can hang and play until they are fully vaccinated. 

The adoption fee for this dog is $375, which helps with the cost of routine vet care. This fee DOES NOT INCLUDE spay/neuter if the pup is not already spayed/neutered. If the animal you are adopting is not already spayed/neutered, you will be required to sign a contract legally obligating you to have the animal altered. ***Note that puppy adoption fees most often help generate revenue that goes towards older, special needs animals that need our help. Surgeries, heartworm treatment, boarding costs....all things that often result in adoptable dogs and cats being left behind to be euthanized. So adopting a puppy saves not just one life, but many! 

Puppies require an adopter who is home a good part of the day to continue their training - no exceptions! They are up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines and preventatives and will need to be spayed/neutered at the age of 6 months. Please note, this pup's immune system will not be fully functioning until about 16 weeks of age and therefore, s/he is not suited for Apartment/Condo living or Town homes without a private fenced yard and will not be able to go to public places where s/he could possibly be exposed to the germs of unvaccinated dogs, such as PetSmart/PetCo and dog parks until s/he is 16 weeks old

For more information, please email fbognon@petconnectrescue.org

animal.description:
Meet adorable Juneau! He and his sisters arrived into PetConnect's care a week ago and are thriving in their foster homes. The sweeties are typical playful, loving puppies! They would love a home with another pup to play with, but they'd also be okay as an only dog. They will do well with respectful children. They will need a home with someone around during the day to continue to work with them on their housetraining and socializing. They will also need a home with a private yard where they can hang and play until they are fully vaccinated. 

The adoption fee for this dog is $375, which helps with the cost of routine vet care. This fee DOES NOT INCLUDE spay/neuter if the pup is not already spayed/neutered. If the animal you are adopting is not already spayed/neutered, you will be required to sign a contract legally obligating you to have the animal altered. ***Note that puppy adoption fees most often help generate revenue that goes towards older, special needs animals that need our help. Surgeries, heartworm treatment, boarding costs....all things that often result in adoptable dogs and cats being left behind to be euthanized. So adopting a puppy saves not just one life, but many! 

Puppies require an adopter who is home a good part of the day to continue their training - no exceptions! They are up-to-date on age appropriate vaccines and preventatives and will need to be spayed/neutered at the age of 6 months. Please note, this pup's immune system will not be fully functioning until about 16 weeks of age and therefore, s/he is not suited for Apartment/Condo living or Town homes without a private fenced yard and will not be able to go to public places where s/he could possibly be exposed to the germs of unvaccinated dogs, such as PetSmart/PetCo and dog parks until s/he is 16 weeks old

For more information, please email fbognon@petconnectrescue.org

animal.description:
Born approximately January 2011, Wilbur is a very special male Terrier mix, seeking a very special home or family. Here is a little bit about him: Wilbur is one of the most gentle loving dogs we have ever come in contact with. He came to us very sick and is gradually gaining his strength and love of life back. Just after Wilbur came into the rescue he had all of his teeth removed so he will need a soft food diet or kibble very well soaked. Wilbur startles very easy as his eyes aren't as good as they once were. He gets along with all humans and dogs alike. Wilbur would thrive in a home with another dog of similar size and energy level, with a family who is home a lot (in other words that doesn't leave him for long stretches of time). He sleeps most of his days and gets small bursts of energy that he spends galloping around. Wilbur will struggle with a dog door as he is very leery of a door not being wide open. Wilbur is the bestest boy and deserves a home that will show him unconditional love! A secure fence with adults or adults and children over 5. Applications can be accessed at www.mikeyschance.com

No children under 5. 

Like all Mikey's Chance dogs, this dog will come to you from a foster home that has provided loving one-on-one attention, socialization and some basic training, as well as quality food and exercise. 

Applications can be found at www.mikeyschance.com and completed on a computer, tablet, and/or phone. Please note that adopters are not chosen on a first come, first served basis, but full consideration is given to the best fit for the dog AND the adopter. Applications can take up to 3 weeks to process. Application submission DOES NOT guarantee approval for adoption.

animal.description:
Basil is a super cute 6-year-old Cocker Spaniel mix that weighs 17 pounds. He is the sweetest little guy that will make the perfect companion for anyone! He loves exploring the backyard, playing with other dogs, doesn't mind cats, and is very social. He has never met a stranger! He would do best in a home without small children, but he loves older considerate children. He is potty trained, leash trained, and knows some tricks! His favorite pose is to sit on his hind legs like a meerkat! He is neutered, vaccinated, heartworm negative, and microchipped. He is $400 plus TX sales tax with an approved application: www.recycledpomsbcs.com/adopt

Texas law requires that all humane organizations (Rescues, SPCA's, Humane Societies, State nonprofit, and charitable 501c3 exempt orgs) collect and remit sales and use tax to the Texas Comptroller on their adoption fees.

We do not ship or transport our dogs. We require all adopters to meet the dog in person to ensure it is a good fit. We represent the dog to the best of our ability and since they are in rescue, we do not always get their history.

Please note: We are a non-profit Pomeranian Rescue with dogs in private foster homes. We do not have a facility open to the public. We require an approved application before a potential adopter is introduced to a dog. We contact vet references to ensure animals in the home are current on vaccinations, heart worm prevention, and sterilization. We do not adopt our dogs to homes in which an animal is not spayed or neutered. A home visit may be required.

Please visit our website for more information and an adoption application. www.recycledpomsbcs.com

animal.description:
Remington is a charming and goofy 3 year old Husky! He is full of personality and there is never a dull (or quiet!) moment when he is around! Some huskies could do with or without their humans, but Remington prefers to be around his people, soaking up all of the love like a fluffy sponge! When you meet Remington, you will find that he is full of life and his never-ending optimism is an absolute pleasure to be around! He is social and friendly with all dogs and cats! Yes…even cats! 

This stunning, young boy experienced a spinal stroke (Fibrocartilaginous Embolism) 4 months ago and is now paralyzed in the hind end. Despite months of Acupuncture, Laser Therapy, and Hydrotherapy, Remington was not able to regain the use of his hind legs. But don’t tell him that! He now has a set of wheels, and he will run circles around you any day of the week! He loves to go on walks and explore all that the Pacific Northwest has to offer! Due to his hind end paralysis, Remington does not know when he has to go potty (he is incontinent). His incontinence is easily managed by expressing his bladder 3-4 times per day. As long as this is accomplished, he will not leak urine in between expressions and does not require a belly band. Remington is grateful for the help and will hold perfectly still for you! He scoots freely around the house during the day, and he is crate trained for sleeping at night. 

Remington deserves the chance to have a forever family to call his own, so if you are interested in adopting this handsome guy, please read more about our adoption process and fill out an application on our website at www.heathshavenrescue.com! He is already neutered, microchipped, current on vaccines/flea & tick preventative, and crate trained…all he needs is a loving home! 

**We do adopt out of state as long as a home visit can be completed and transport can be arranged. Remington is too big to fly in the cabin of a plane (and we do not fly our special needs dogs as "cargo") so ground  transport is the only option for him.

animal.description:
Hello, my name is Mufasa (HWTH#21026A).  I am a Lab mix, born on 10/4/2010 and I weigh approximately 45 lbs.  My mother Diamond (adopted), my sister Lady (HWTH#21027A), and I were relinquished together to Halfway to Home after our owner passed away.  We are a little overwhelmed after having being taken from the only home we have ever known, but the people here are very nice and are helping us prepare to find new homes to spend our golden years.  I may be a senior, but I have a puppy-like spirit.  I am a little overweight but with properly-portioned good-quality kibble and regular exercise that spirit will live on and on. 
Senior dogs make wonderful companions because unlike puppies, we don't need a lot of exercise, we are good at entertaining ourselves, we understand the difference between a dog toy and your shoes, and adjust easily to your schedule so you will get a good night's sleep!  I would be an ideal friend for a retired individual or couple who enjoys going for leisurely walks and having a loyal buddy laying at their feet.  I have been around children, other dogs, and even cats for most of my life so I would be a good fit for most families (little children might be a little much).  My exercise needs are moderate so although a home with fenced yard would be great, I might be ok in a ground-floor apartment or condo as long as I have an outdoor space to do my business and you are willing to take me for a couple of short walks daily.  More than anything else I am looking for a family to love me  and that I can love back.  How does that sound?  If you would like more information or would like to make an appointment to meet me, please call Sandy at tele#661-824-4495 (this is a landline).  Thank you and I hope to see you soon.

animal.description:
PIPER, along with her running buddy Tipper, also posted on this Petfinder page, was picked up as a stray by Animal Control in Lauderdale County, TN. Because Piper and Tipper are such sweet tempered dogs, the Lauderdale County Animal Shelter kept them in a quiet place within the shelter instead of keeping them in the general population. Grace Rescue was asked please to take both into rescue, and we were happy to be able to oblige. Both of these Beagle babies are wonderful dogs.

Piper is a pocket Beagle weighing only about 21 pounds and is estimated to be about 5 years old. She is NOT a senior Beagle snd has not even lived half of her life expectancy. Our oldest personal Beagle is 17 years old. 

She has been microchipped, spayed, and our vet also did dentals at the same time to save putting Piper under anesthesia a second time. She had an abscessed tooth that needed immediate care. Her bloodwork looks GREAT, and overall she is fairly healthy. 

Piper is not available for regular adoption until she completes heartworm treatment; however, we ARE accepting applications for foster-to-adopt through heartworm treatment. That means that the family who fosters her through heartworm treatment will be given priority in the adoption process. We have never done that before COVID quarantines, but our Hayley, Millie and Gracie, all 3 are in foster homes through heartworm treatment, and it is a blessing to everyone. 

If you think you are the right family for Piper and are interested in fostering her through complete vetting, we would be so happy to send you an adoption application. Since we never permit someone to foster that we would not approve as an adopter, we ask that potential fosters complete the same adoption application as adopters. After all, the family approved for fostering would be given top priority for adopting. So, please email Diana at dmoore2003@bellsouth.net for an application. During COVID times, we are inundated with adoption application requests for all of our Beagles, so please be a serious adopter before requesting our adoption application—that you are willing to complete and submit an application for consideration. We hope to hear from you about this precious Beagle girl.

animal.description:
Meet Stella!
*BREED EXPERIENCE REQUIRED*
**HEARTWORM POSITIVE - Currently being treated*

Breed: German Shepherd
Estimated DOB: 01/10/2018
Sex: Female - Spayed
Weight: 60 lbs 
Rescued From: MS

Things to know about Stella:
- Sweet Stella has been living her life in a pen & her rescuer immediately thought of TLC to help give her that second chance
- Shy & timid but very very sweet! 
- Stella will need a patient adopter with GSD experience who can show her the world isn't such a scary place
- Like any GSD, Stella is looking for her person to bond with 
- Bonds quickly to her person and will seek out attention
- Learning toys are fun
- Walks well on leash
- Loves going for walks
- Crate Trained - Loves her crate, this is her safe place
- Working on housebreaking 
- Dog friendly 
- Has not been assessed with cats yet
- Looking for a home where she can settle in and learn what being loved feels like

Apply to adopt Stella at www.tlcrescuepa.com/adopt
Consider donating to support Stella's care at https://donorbox.org/ExtraTLC

What you should know about a Heartworm Positive Dog:
Over 250,000 dogs are diagnosed with Heartworm Disease each & every year.  Heartworm is a mosquito transmitted, preventable disease. Fortunately, there is both a preventative and a cure for Heartworm. While treatment is a costly, 4 month long process, prevention is an inexpensive, once-a-month chewable. TLC covers the cost of each dog’s heartworm treatment, as well as provides support to ensure the best quality of life for our pups. Once cured, most dogs go on to lead a happy & healthy life! The key to this happiness is that once-a-month heartworm preventative, in which you can receive directly from your veterinarian.  To learn more about Heartworm Disease, prevention & treatment, please visit www.heartwormsociety.org.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.*DEAF*From the foster mom: Sadie is very timid at first and reluctant to cuddle up but once she knows it's ok, she loves to be cuddled! She is a velcro dog. Deaf dogs need to see you to look for visuals and to remain comfortable in their new surroundings and she is no exception. She will bark when in her area if she cannot see you, she will bark every time if you go back and forth if she catches a glimpse of you. She will stop barking and go lay in her kennel once she realizes you aren't coming back in sight. Deaf dogs are heavy sleepers and it's best to softly touch them when waking them up...or sometimes I lightly stomp of the floor. The vibrations help them know someone is there. Also when approaching her...I smile, and do a wave. Thumbs up means good girl, and normal hand commands one might use for sit, stay and lay down (I always throw some other signs in I know for deaf dogs) but to each their own. She is VERY treat motivated and know's sit,shake, and stay. I gave her a bath already, and I'm sure she'll get another at the vet. She did well in the tub. She has had zero potty accidents in the house. She does enjoy someone outside with her(probably cause it's still new) but will go in and out one her own in my fenced yard. She does ok with the kids, but it's good to keep an eye on her when she's around kids -- deaf dogs (at least the one's I've had here) seem to paw more than my hearing dogs, and they are face level to kids and can hurt them if it's unexpected. I feed her 4 times a day. 1 cup about every 4 hours. Im not sure if that's a lot, but she's on the skinny side, and it not disagreeing with her. Over all she's a very nice boxer girl.

animal.description:
This compact-size lover-boy was brought to Colorado after a bunch of dogs on streets of New Mexico attacked him. He was saved by volunteers, treated for his leg injury, and now has comfortable settled in his foster home and ready to bring some joy to you, his future family! 

Elijah is a mellow pit mix dog with loving personality, he is particularly good at giving kisses! He is a happy camper outside on a walk or a very long walk, but is also content curling up next to you (or on you) for a sweet nap! He is learning fast and pretty smart, he will need to continued training and getting better on the leash, of course. Gentle leader worked wonders! He is playful too, but could be dog-selective due to his past misfortune. He likes foster’s resident female dog, but she is 14 and playing is really a nuisance for her due to her golden age. So when he gets bored he tries to play with cats, which they graciously decline ? Since the male dogs attacked him, he is cautionary about making friends with male dogs, but given his friendly demeanor and some patience, he will overcome this fear for sure, he is good with females.  He is house trained, given opportunity to go out regularly, not a chewer, unless it’s a smelly cow hoof or tears, not a barker, has gentle mouth, and still needs to learn some basic manners. Oh, he gets along with 3 resident cats! What a catch! 
Since he is at young age of around a year- year-and-half, he would love to find a worthy playmate. Though he loves his Hoomans so much, that if there is someone who will provide activities, stimulating his curiosity and spend time with him, he might be ok as well. He sleeps in his crate through the night and doesn’t mind it a bit. No anxiety, but of course, he would rather sleep in your bed! He probably will leak the little ones to death, but still jumps when excited, so it might not be ideal with young kids. 
Elijah is truly a wonderful,  loving, easy going, well responding to positive stimulation and easily redirect able, eager to please dog. He will return trifold your kindness and love if you give  him a chance! Take that chance!!! Apply at fromforgottentoforever.com/adoptionapplication/.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.From the foster mom -- Deuce is such a good boy! He is coming into his own. He is really low maintenance. The first few days I wondered, are they sure he's not deaf? He responds better to hand signals then commands. Maybe he cant understand our Minnesota accents! He doesn't mind the snow. The cat and Deuce have warmed up to each other. I've given him a little more freedom. Yesterday Deuce helped me do laundry so he went up and down the steps a lot. All in all, he's getting good exercise. He likes his walks, he doesn't pull on the leash. He doesn't seem to have any hip or joint issues that we can tell from petting and manipulating his legs. I tried to put some earwash on a cotton ball to clean his ears and found out he did NOT like it. Deuce doesn't beg for food, you can eat in front of him and doesn't surf the counters or get into anything. He's pretty smart, he can open doors (bathroom) if you don't close them all the way. Deuce is fine in his crate. He really could care less about toys at this point in time. I put a camera on when we left the house to see how he does all alone -- took a nap and waited for us to get back. What a easy peasy precious boxer boy!

This sweet, affectionate girl needed to be rescued because she tested positive for heartworm! Of course, we had to make her a diamond! Now she is in a loving foster home and on her way to the happy, healthy life she deserves.

We just need to find her furever home - could it be yours?

Kaiyah's foster family adores her! She is crate trained and house trained. She loves going for daily walks and is working on her leash manners. She also enjoys a snooze on the couch or on your lap. Kaiyah sometimes gets curious about things outside of her fenced yard. Her family will need to make sure she cannot get out and investigate any sights or sounds that catch her interest!

Kaiyah loves being around her people, including older, respectful kids. She cannot live with cats, but she has gotten along with some dogs she has met that are her size. A meet and greet with any resident or frequently visiting dogs is required.

Show Kaiyah the love she deserves! Make her a part of your family by applying to adopt today!

Adoption donation includes Spay/Neuter, UTD on Vaccinations, deworming, and flea treatment.

animal.description:
*We are not hosting adoption events at Petco for the public at this time*
We are currently very busy and have over 100 applications to review and on file. Thank you for your patience! We are working to find everyone a companion. 

Princess Ruby is an adorable 9 week old Hound/Black Mouth cur mix. These puppies are huge!! 

If you are interested in adopting the first step is to fill out an adoption application on our website aaanimalrescue.org. We are currently very busy! Please reach out to allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com if you have an approved application on file! Please fill out an adoption application on our website if you are ready to adopt! 

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time! We are on a mission to find everyone companions, we will continue to rescue dogs weekly! We update our page every Monday evening. We are not currently hosting any Petco adoption events for the public. We will be hosting meet/greet adoption appointments!


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.
animal.name: Princess Ruby

*We are not hosting adoption events at Petco for the public at this time*
We are currently very busy and have over 100 applications to review and on file. Thank you for your patience! We are working to find everyone a companion. 

Twiggy is an adorable 9 week old Hound/Black Mouth cur mix. These puppies are huge!! 

If you are interested in adopting the first step is to fill out an adoption application on our website aaanimalrescue.org. We are currently very busy! Please reach out to allaboardanimalrescue@gmail.com if you have an approved application on file! Please fill out an adoption application on our website if you are ready to adopt! 

Thank you for your patience and understanding during this difficult time! We are on a mission to find everyone companions, we will continue to rescue dogs weekly! We update our page every Monday evening. We are not currently hosting any Petco adoption events for the public. We will be hosting meet/greet adoption appointments!


Breed and size disclosure: As a rescue all of our dogs come to us from high-kill shelters or other rescues, so we do not get a lot of background or information on these dogs. We occasionally receive the mother with the puppies, but in most cases both parents are unknown. Because of this we do not know the full breeding of the dogs. We are required to list the dogs based on the breeds provided to us on their records, but they are all mixed breeds as far as we know, and we cannot guarantee the actual breeds of any of these dogs. Since the full breeding of the dogs is unknown we can also only give you an educated guess on the full-grown size of the dogs. All of the current information we have on the dogs is listed in their bio above. More information may be available at our adoption event, since a lot of the fosters turn in report cards on how the dog has done in their care when they drop them off. 

Adoption Process: If you are interested in adopting from us, the first step of our adoption process is to fill out an application online at http://aaanimalrescue.org/adoption_app.html. It takes us 24-48 hours to process your application and get back to you, via email. Applications turned in Friday afternoon or Saturday morning will not be processed since we are preparing for or at our adoption event. We do have applications on site at our events, but are not always able to approve them at that time and many of the dogs will already have holds on them, so we suggest you fill out an application prior to attending an adoption event. We can place a hold on one dog per approved applicant after a deposit fee has been received, please do not ask to hold a dog if you have not turned in an application and been approved, for the first hour of our adoption event, so that they can get the first chance to meet and hopefully adopt that dog. After the first hour of the event all dogs are available on a first come, first serve basis. If you already have an approved application on file, there will just be more paperwork and the adoption fee at the event, but you will be able to take home the dog/puppy that day. Since we are foster based and do not have a location, our dogs are only available to meet at our events, unless otherwise noted.

animal.description:
Say hello to this sweet fluff ball Pharaoh!! He is a 2 year old Chow mix who currently weights 62lbs. Pharaoh is a very affectionate, lovable boy! He enjoys playing with his foster sister, doing sprints in the backyard and cuddling with his foster mom and the little boy in the house. Pharaoh does great in his crate, walks well on a leash and he is house trained. Overall he is a perfect boy looking for the perfect family!!  Pharaoh's adoption fee is $250.00.

To adopt this pet, please visit https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt

All of our dogs come spayed or neutered, fully up to date on vaccinations, including rabies (if age appropriate) and bordetella, are microchipped, heartworm negative, current on flea/tick and heartworm prevention, dewormed, and treated for any ailments found upon veterinary examination. The adoption fee covers a portion of these services, and makes it possible for us to continue rescuing animals.  

For more information on the adoption fees and the adoption process, please complete our adoption application here: https://www.louieslegacy.org/adopt - an application allows us to get to know your family better so we can assess whether the animal you are interested in is a good match for your home. An application does not obligate you to adopt. Please understand that due to the volume of applications some animals receive, we are unable to contact all applicants. If your application is considered a good fit for the dog you are interested in, or even a different pet, a volunteer will give you a call as soon as possible.  

We are a foster based rescue and do not have a shelter location where dogs can be seen during the week. Please see our Facebook page at https://www.facebook.com/LouiesLegacy for our weekly adoption album if you are interested in meeting a dog in person. Not all animals attend every adoption event, please check our Facebook page for animal event times and locations before you make a trip to meet a specific animal.

Thanks so much for caring about a needy animal!

animal.description:
**Click on the link https://www.patreon.com/AlmostHome to Become a Patron! For only $5 a month you can read wonderful stories about the animals who have come through our program. everything from how we got started to cruelty and rehabilitation cases. This money goes directly to caring for the animals in our program as well as helps save others desperately needing rescue. Thank you in advance - we seriously could not do what we do without your support. 

**IMPORTANT!!  Please read the entire bio before contacting us with questions. Send us an email requesting an application to start the adoption process adopt@almosthomenm.org   Make sure you add our address to your safe sender list or watch your junk/spam emails.  For more photos please visit our Facebook page.   http://www.facebook.com/pages/Almost-Home-New-Mexico/203840136304815 

Approximate DOB 5/26/2011

Size - Medium about 40 lbs

History- Merlin was rescued about 7 years ago by a wonderful couple. He has lived with him and has been awesome with everyone he meets. He is a perfect gentleman at all times. However, recently the family has had some losses and due to family health issues and obligations feel Merlin is not getting the love and attention he had become accustomed to. They love him dearly and want the best for him so they have reached out to us in hopes of finding him a family that can give him the one on one attention and love he craves. 

Temperament- Very sweet, gentle, and loving. Really a perfect dog.

Energy Level- Still pretty active despite his age. Is not a jogger but would love walks and hanging with a loved one on the couch. 

Dogs/Cats- He has met several dogs as they were avid fosters and have a boarding kennel as well. He loves playing with everyone big or small. I believe he has a high prey drive though so cannot be with chickens, ducks, or rabbits - he will kill them. I will ask if he has been around cats. 

Housetrained- He is perfect. Uses a dog door on his own. Never marks in the house. Just the best boy ever.

Merlin is pretty much the best dog someone could want. He is perfectly behaved. Does not jump on you, or get under foot. I've never heard him bark though I am sure he does when people pull up but stops quickly. He is perfect for the groomer. He would be great for someone at home who likes walks, playing, and cuddles. He does need to stay on a schedule with a groomer due to his coat but other than that one thing he is a seriously amazing dog.

Adoption fee $200 includes neuter, age appropriate vaccinations (4 for puppies), deworming, microchip, rabies, collar and leash, training information, and all the support you need. 

Send us an e-mail to adopt@almosthomenm.org requesting an application to adopt this sweetie!! Animals are seen by appointment only. An application must be submitted to us prior to making an appointment. We do give a discount when adopting multiple pets.

If you would like to donate to our cause and help care for the animals in our care please visit our main website www.almosthomenm.org and click on the donate button at the top left of the screen..

Meet Mr Gimpy. The name might not politically correct but this boy is full of so much love he doesn’t care what you call him so long as it’s done with love. He came from the mean streets of Mexico where his foot was run over by a car and left unattended.  Once he arrived with the rescue we had x-rays done and found that the bones are completely crushed and there is no saving it. He is scheduled for an amputation on the first. We are desperately searching for a foster for him so he does not have to be in a kennel environment after the surgery. 

He is approximately four years old and 20 pounds of pure love.  He gets along with all size dogs. And although he might not look like a corgi in the pictures that you met him in person with his little nub tail you’ll see the breed in him. 

We are still getting to know him but so far everything we found out about him we absolutely adore. He’s a very resilient boy who just wants to give and receive love. 

If you would like to meet him please fill out an application. 

https://www.muttsinneed.org/adoption-application.html

animal.description:
PLEASE READ: The clinics are not open for viewing animals. If you are interested in meeting this pet, please email information about yourself, family, residence and current/prior pet experience. If it is a good fit you will be sent an application. Once that is approved, arrangements will be made for a meeting. Thanks for your understanding!

Meet Shelby, a 1.5 year old Husky mix. He is a sweet and handsome boy, very friendly. Shelby is a LOT of dog, 73 lbs and very high energy. He will need a new family who will appreciate his size and energy, and give him tasks and outlets to make him the best dog he can be. His adoption fee is $229 and includes his neuter, microchip, routine labwork, and microchip. Please email us to start the adoption process.

Email inquires can be directed to availablepets@gmail.com.
Adoption donations for adult dogs range from $59 to $299 and puppies from $159 to $599. This includes: 
-  Spay or neuter surgery
Vaccines current to the date of adoption*: 
  -  Rabies vaccine
  -  Bordatella vaccine
  -  Booster for canine Distemper, Adenovirus type 1 & 2, Leptospirosis,
      Parainfluenza, Parvovirus, and Coronavirus (DHLPPC)
  - Canine Influenza vaccine
-  Fecal test
-  1st worming 
-  Heartworm test (+6 months old) 
-  Capstar flea treatment
-  Microchip identification implant
* Boosters required for puppies and kittens (depending on age) POST adoption are the responsibility of the pet owner.
 
Heartworm prevention must also be purchased at the time of adoption and prices vary depending on the size of the animal being adopted.  Puppies under 6 months old are required to sign up for a puppy obedience class. ($89 deposit required, refundable upon completion)

Come Ready to Adopt: 
If you rent or live in a condo/townhouse with an association, bring your lease/bylaws indicating pets are allowed and if there are any restrictions. We require vaccinations and tests to be up to date for the protection of your current pets. Bringing their vet records can help speed the adoption process. All adults in the household must be present and co-sign the application.

Eddison is from a litter we had this past summer. His family is no longer able to keep him. He is a very sweet boy. He loves to snuggle and done well with everyone he has been introduced to. He loves to play out in the snow with Hudson and does fairly well on the leash. He seems to have basic commands down but would benefit from training. He appears to be housebroken and crate trained but we always recommend a refresher in his new home. 

He does chew and would benefit from training to work on this. Also recommended that he has plenty of toys and other things for him to chew on. 

Eddison does not like hard floors so he will need some time to learn how to use them if you have them. We are currently working on it with him. He is getting better every day and is now exploring the house more.

animal.description:
If you are looking for the happiest, most social dog Laila is your girl! This girl has never met a stranger and is always so happy to meet new people and other dogs. She gets so excited that her whole butt wags! She loves her toys and she has some puppy energy but once she wears herself out she is the BEST cuddle partner. She's a very smart puppy and any additional training should be a breeze for her. She's doing great with potty training and we're working on crate training. She will cry for a few minutes when she first goes in but then she settles down quietly, especially if she has treats or toys to keep her busy. She does have some skin allergies to certain grasses that could require allergy medication depending on your lifestyle and location. Regular baths and short periods of time outside help to manager her allergies. Laila is a pitbull mix with an estimated dob 10/20/2020. She was found abandoned in a creek with her siblings at about 6 weeks old. She is currently 18 lbs at 14 weeks old.

Laila is available for adoption with Saving Grace Dog Rescue of San Antonio. The adoption fee is $150.00. An adoption application, home visit and adoption contract are all required. All dogs are spayed/neutered, up to date on vaccinations appropriate for their age, microchipped, and wormed for internal and external parasites. If you would like more information or an adoption application, please email us at sgdrsa@outlook.com.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **
Gaia is a beautiful 3-year-old Great Dane. She is an active and playful dog and her ideal home would be able to provide her with appropriate daily exercise and training. Because of her size, she would not be suitable for a home with smaller dogs as they may find her rough play as overwhelming.
Please understand you are committing to providing a good home for her entire life (up to 15+ years or more.)

You must be committed to housebreaking, age-appropriate enrichment and exercise, leash training, grooming needs, and positive socialization.

Her adoption fee is $300. This includes her spay surgery, rabies vaccination, Nobivac Canine 1-DAPP vaccination, Nobivac Intra-Trac 3 vaccination, Drontal Plus, Tri-Heart Plus Chewable Tablet, IDEXX SNAP 4Dx Plus Test, 24PetWatch microchip, leash and collar, and a trial offer for 24PetWatch Pet Insurance.

Please be aware that puppies and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so interested parties are encouraged to apply online at www.saspca.org.

Please ensure your application is complete before submitting. We do verify property ownership, landlord references, apartment/HOA restrictions, veterinary references, and criminal histories.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio TX 78232. Event hours are 11:00 a.m. to 3:00 p.m.

Additional questions may be directed to sagdinfo@gmail.com.

** This dog is in a foster home in San Antonio, TX. Prospective adopters must be able to travel to San Antonio to complete the adoption process. Please apply online at http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/ **

- IMPORTANT INFORMATION -

SASPCA Homeward Bound Dog Rescue and San Antonio Great Dane Rescue are 501(c)(3) foster-based rescue groups based in San Antonio, Texas.

Our group focuses on assisting open admission shelters in South Texas where over 32,000 dogs and cats are euthanized each year.

Our puppies and dogs are completely vetted and live in foster homes. They are spayed/neutered, vaccinated, microchipped, dewormed, and tested for heartworm disease.All adoptions include one month of flea and heartworm preventative, leash and collar, and opportunity to enroll in a 30-day trial of pet insurance.

Our adoption events are held each Saturday at Petco located in the Northwoods Shopping Center at 18138 San Pedro Ave, San Antonio, TX 78232. Event hours are typically 11:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m.

We also host additional adoption events throughout the year. Please visit our Facebook pages for the most current event schedules.

https://m.facebook.com/HomewardBoundDogRescue/?tsid=0.11494693985281179&source=typeahead

https://m.facebook.com/profile.php?id=185497084826453&tsid=0.7626298417270982&source=typeahead

If your adoption application is approved and you are traveling from out-of-town, we hold your chosen pet for one hour past the event start time to allow for travel time.

We are an all-volunteer organization and do not currently have the resources to process out-of-state adoptions.

Our puppies, purebred dogs, and small breed dogs do get adopted quickly so we encourage interested parties to apply online.

Please apply here:

http://texasgreatdane.org/adoption-application/

Somer has been diagnosed with heartworm infection. Dogs acquire heartworm infections when they are bitten by a mosquito that was infected with heartworm larvae.Dogs with heartworm infection live happy, high quality lives as long as they are given appropriate care. Heartworm infection is relatively common in the United States so we are in need of caring adopters like you that are willing to open their home to a dog with heartworm infection. We think that our heartworm dogs have just as much to offer their new adopters as any other dog and they deserve a chance at life. Adopters will receive all the necessary medications needed to complete the heartworm treatment protocol.
