If you are interested in adopting this dog, please download and complete an Adoption Questionnaire from our website and email US at michelel@k-9lifesavers.org
You can learn about the adoption process and find a Word, PDF and ONLINE version of the questionnaire by visiting: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/howtoadopt/.
Dog's Name: Baby Kira
Estimated Breed: Plott Hound MIX
Approximate Age: 8 WEEKS
Approximate Weight: 8-10 lbs
Currently Living at: foster
Adoption Fee: $375
DOG'S DESCRIPTION:
Sweet Kira is hoping a nice family will see her photo and fall in love. She will need a little patience as she learns right from wrong, as all puppies do. She loves to be cuddled, and plays well with the dogs at her foster home. She will love you unconditionally as you teach her. Are you her loving family that will give her a forever home?
Your new pet will require a refresher in house-training. K-9 Lifesavers strongly recommends all new adopters enroll their new pet into obedience training. This provides for an easier transition into a new home, ensures the dog remains well socialized, and helps form a bond between the dog and the new family.
Adoption fees cover basic vetting, rabies (if puppy is old enough), distemper/parvo vaccinations, treatment for worms, heartworm testing (if puppy is old enough), monthly heartworm prevention while in our care, monthly flea/tick prevention while in our care, and our transport costs. As part of the adoption agreement, adopters agree to get the pup spayed/neutered and provide K-9 Lifesavers with proof of spay/neuter. K-9 Lifesavers does not cover the cost of spay/neuter for puppies 6 months or younger.
Foster Program: Foster homes provide for the temporary care of a rescue until the dog is placed into a loving, forever home. For more information on becoming a foster parent, and our Foster Program, visit http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/foster/ or email our Foster Coordinator at foster@k-9lifesavers.org
Help Save Lives! Make a tax-deductible donation today and help save a life. Donations help us offset boarding costs and additional medical treatment for those dogs who need it. K-9 Lifesavers receives NO federal funding and survive with your generous support! We are all volunteer based organization so every cent from your donation goes directly to the dogs in our care.
For more information on K-9 Lifesavers, or to view a complete listing of all our Adoptable Dogs, visit our website at www.k-9lifesavers.org.
Check out our social media! Search for us on Facebook, Twitter, Pinterest and Instagram!!
Thank you for considering a rescue dog!
SPONSOR ME!
Visit: http://www.k-9lifesavers.org/donate/

animal.description:
Meet Orca! This big girl weighs in at around 130 pounds at 3 years old. Orca is a shy girl looking for a patient home that will work with her and help her continue to boost her confidence. She gets more confident with each passing day, and has learned the joys of squeaky toys and doing zoomies! She is fostered with other dogs but prefers those on the medium-large side; no small dogs, please! Her smallest friend is about 45 pounds. She is crate trained, but is working on potty training. Orca is very food motivated and loves to receive cheese as treats. She's a leaner, loving to lean into her foster mom while receiving pets. Orca is working on getting comfortable on the leash. Due to this, she is looking for a home with a fenced in yard and is not suitable for apartment life. She knows how to sit and is working on giving paw! She tends to get overwhelmed easily, so she is looking for an adult only household, as she is not a fan of kids' loud noises and quick movements. Orca's lack of confidence is something her forever family should be prepared to work on. If you think your household is the right place to help Orca blossom, apply online today!

My adoption fee is $250.

animal.description:
MEET LIBERTY!

Liberty is a 7+ year old pittie with a very unique story. This poor girl was abandoned at a local high school football field completely terrified! It took a few days, but a couple dedicated dog-lovers worked to gain her trust enough to get her contained. Once she realized she was safe, she melted back into the sweetest girl who will now make a great addition to just about any home!

Liberty was super skinny when she joined us but has plumped up nicely in her foster home. She's a healthy girl who received a dental cleaning and was spayed and received a clean bill of health from our vet. She is currently living with other dogs, cats and children! She gets along with everyone great. She adores her foster family and will happily snuggle up on the couch (or in bed if allowed). In fact, she can get comfortable just about anywhere! We think Liberty will just need a little time to settle into her future home, as she gets a bit shy and nervous in new situations but given the chance, settles in quickly and will be your best friend in no time!

Liberty is available for adoption through City of Elderly Love! She is spayed, vaccinated and microchipped. Interested in adopting her? Visit www.cityofelderlylove.org to complete an online adoption questionnaire or email us at info@cityofelderlylove.org!

She is about one year old and weighs around 35 to 40 pounds. She is just a little shy still and has no obvious health or behavioral problems that we are aware of. She should be good with kids and most other dogs. With any of our dogs, it’s a good idea for potential adopters with other dogs at home to bring them out to meet the potential adoptee dog before making a final decision.
BEXLEY would make a great indoor/outdoor dog. She has short hair and will not tolerate cold weather very well. She should at least be allowed to sleep indoors and be brought in during cold, wet or stormy weather during the day if possible. She should have plenty of water and good shade if left outside in the summer. She would make a great companion for watching TV and seems to have quite a bit of stamina for jogging or walking.
BEXLEY is looking for a chance at a forever home.

If you would like to meet BEXLEY for a possible adoption, please call (806) 891-0829 from 9 to 5; if (806) 891-0829 doesn’t answer, call (806) 894-6164 and tell them you are interested in adopting a dog. You may need to refer to BEXLEY by her shelter number, D21-01025, when talking to an Animal Control employee.

Harley came to us from JAX Animal Care and Protective Services where he was originally picked up as a stray in December. Unfortunately, Harley was returned to the shelter due to his elderly adopter going into an assisted living facility. Now he is a Faithful Friend looking for his forever home. 
Harley can be a bit shy at first, but is a very sweet guy who loves attention. He has been fine with other dogs that we've introduced him to, but is new to the program so we are still getting to know him. 
Harley has been clean in his crate, but we do not know if he is housebroken. Harley should be fine with older/calm kids, but young/noisy kids will likely make him nervous.

Please visit our website at faithfulfriendsrescue.org/adoptable-pets if you are interested in adopting.

We are setting up adoptions with approved adopters on an appointment basis. We are no longer hosting adoption events at PetSmart until further notice. We are not arranging meet and greets; but appointments to finalize adoptions to limit exposure for all. Our adoptions come with a one week trial period in which if things are not working out, we will refund your adoption fee if you decide to return your newly adopted Faithful Friend. Our adoptions must be done in person and we do not arrange transport to adopters. Our adoption fees vary and we are only able to accept payments by card* at this time but include spay/neuter, heartworm test (dogs), FeLV/FIV test (cats), age appropriate vaccines and deworming, flea, tick and heartworm medication and microchip.

Luna is a very “young” 6-8 year old German Shepherd mix. She may have had a rough start, being tied outside in all weather, but she's settling into domesticated life like a pro!  She loves to cuddle up on the couch!  She's smart and has already learned sit, stay (mostly), and shake. She's totally potty trained and scratches the door to let you know she needs to go out (or barks when crated to alert).  Having been an outside dog for all her life until now, she does still need to learn some manners, like not to bark at visitors or jump in excitement when you come home. She's also very interested in food and likes to share your food, so you may need to crate her during meals. She loves to play with squeaky toys, balls, you name it. She's good with kids and other dogs, but quickly made clear she wants to be top dog, so if you already have a top dog that doesn't like to share, she might not be the right fit for you. She's a sweet, cuddle bug!

Heart-worm negative, current on vaccines.  If not already spayed/neutered - it is included in adoption fee.

animal.description:
****If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder, we are still accepting applications for them. PLEASE READ ENTIRE BIO BEFORE EMAILING****

*Name: Asher
*Age: 7 yrs
*Current Weight: 10lbs
*Adoption fee: $300
*Health: up to date on required vaccines, neutered, has spinal disc compression 

Asher is a very smart quirky guy with a sad past. Asher was found in a dumpster by a good samaritan who then brought him to the local shelter in GA. When he arrived they noticed he had no use of his hind legs. People immediately started to post him on social media to save his life. He had literally 10 minutes left on the clock before he was to be euthanized when SNARR NE stepped in and took him into rescue. He was then transported to NY where his foster mom and physical therapist picked him up and took him to our specialist for immediate surgery. A compressed disc was hindering his ability to walk. Within days post spinal surgery he began to heal and regain the use of this legs. 
He is still on the mend but can walk and climb a ramp all by himself. He does have stiff knees that need massaging and lots of walking will do wonders. He still leaks urine so he does wear a belly band diaper, but will wait to make poop outdoors. 
Asher is a one woman kind of man. He picks his person and that’s who he trusts. Once he’s picked you he will be loyal to no end, but can get snappy with other people. He will love his person strongly, coming running to greet you at the door and wait for you if you leave. He loves to burrow under covers and is a great snuggler. 

The best household for Asher would be someone single with no children who is looking for a companion dog. He likes other dogs and will occasionally participate in play, but really he just likes his person the best. Are you his person?

To apply to adopt Asher, fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. 
**Meet and greets will not be scheduled without an approved application.**

-------------------------------------------------------
FAQs -- PLEASE READ ALL BEFORE EMAILING
-------------------------------------------------------
**Please note that SNARR NE is a volunteer-based organization. While our volunteers will try to respond to you as quickly as possible, it is helpful if you review the following information about our adoption process before emailing:**

- LISTED BREED(S) & AGE: We are taking our best guess on age, breed, and size when fully grown, based on the puppy's/dog's physical appearance and what we might have learned about one or both parents depending on the situation. *NOTE* We rarely know a dog's exact age, nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time. Because we often do not have access to medical records at the time that we are posting dogs to Petfinder, there are sometimes discrepancies between what is posted on Petfinder and what might be listed on a dog's medical records.

- SNARR'S ADOPTION PROCESS: The first step in adopting or meeting a SNARR dog/puppy is to fill out an application at www.snarrnortheast.org/applications. Once we receive your application, one of our adoption application processors will contact you, review our adoption process with you, and answer any additional questions you may have. **We do not go on a first-come-first-serve basis for adoptions, but on best fit for a family and most importantly the puppy or dog.**

- MEETING ADOPTABLE DOGS: Meet and greets will not be scheduled until after your adoption application has been fully processed by one of our adoption processors.

- APPLYING ONLINE: If you fill out an online application, please do so from a computer (not a mobile device), make sure you answer ALL the questions in as much detail as possible, and that you receive a confirmation email. If you do not receive a confirmation email, that means we did NOT receive your application.

- PUPPIES: We do suggest listing a 1st, 2nd and 3rd choice on your application if applying for a puppy with several litter mates.

- ADOPTION FEES:  $495 for puppies / $375 for adults. Adoption Fees for Seniors, Special Needs and Bonded Pairs vary

animal.description:
Hi!! My name is Sherlock and I am a 10 year old, 20lbs Dachshund Terrier mix.

- I was dropped off at the shelter overweight, with failing eyesight, and in need of some serious dental work. However, thanks to my amazing foster parents, I am now in great condition and ready to find my forever home!

- I love everyone! Adults, kids, and dogs alike but would probably prefer to live in a home without young kids since my vision isn’t what it used to be, and kids racing around may confuse me.

- I love going on adventures with you, but bring a backpack so I can take breaks and chill when it gets too intense, as I am still an older man even if I don't look it ;) 

- The past is in the past. Although we're not sure where I came from, I hold no grudges. I am quick to love anyone who will love me and can't wait to kiss you all over and cuddle!!!

- I really love if there's a human, or dog, walking close to me so I can just follow their lead. In fact I will need a home with another dog, so I can feel safe and follow their lead :) 

- I don't have the best vision these days but that just means I’ll never care how you look, just how many pets you'll give me! 

- All the love please! Even though I can't see you coming, I've proven to not be reactive when it comes to physical touch. So...again...all the pets please!!!!!

If you see me online I am still available for adoption! If you are interested in adopting me please fill out an application here: www.hitlivingfoundation.org/adoption-application, and email a video walkthrough of your home and yard to BOTH Nicole@hitlivingfoundation.org AND Marta@hitlivingfoundation.org. Your application will not be counted as valid without your video. You will hear back from us within a few days.

animal.description:
SAGE, shelter number D21-01001, is a female terrier mix. She is about three years old and weighs about 35 pounds. She was surrendered to the shelter by her owner, along with QUEEN ; we are not sure why. She is very shy and has no obvious health problems. She was very scared of the leash, so we did get a picture or two, but we plan to get more later when she has adjusted better to being in the shelter. She did enjoy being petted and when I sat down with her, she crawled into my lap and licked my hand some. She should get more comfortable in a home where she can be shown some love and attention. With any of our dogs, it’s a good idea for potential adopters with other dogs at home to bring them out to meet the potential adoptee dog before making a final decision. SAGE would make a great indoor/outdoor dog. She has short hair and will not tolerate cold weather very well. She should at least be allowed to sleep indoors and be brought in during cold, wet or stormy weather during the day if possible. She should have plenty of water and good shade if left outside in the summer. She would make a great companion for watching TV or just hanging out in the evenings and would love to be included in any family activities indoors or out whenever possible.
SAGE is looking for another chance at a forever home.
Levelland Animal Control is understaffed right now and adoptions are by appointment only. If you would like to meet SAGE for a possible adoption, please call (806) 891-0829 from 9 to 5, Monday through Friday; if (806) 891-0829 doesn’t answer, call (806) 894-6164 and tell them you are interested in adopting a dog. You may need to refer to SAGE by her shelter number, D21-01001, when talking to an Animal Control employee.
Levelland Animal Control is understaffed right now and adoptions are by appointment only.
All our dogs are vaccinated for Parvo, distemper, Bordetella (kennel cough) and most other common dog diseases. We do not vaccinate them for Rabies. There is no adoption fee, but the adopter will be responsible for having the dog spayed or neutered and for the Rabies shot.
Check the Google map for directions to the shelter located at 109 Commerce in Levelland, Texas.

animal.description:
Available: Now
Age: 1 year
Size: Large (70-80lbs)
Energy: Moderate
Gender: Neutered Male
Breed: Pyrenees/Retriever X
Notes: Loyal and Energetic

Adoption fee: $375 (view what’s included at www.manitobaunderdogs.org/adoptionfees)

Hi y’all, my name is Alfie! MUR helped me after some good folks found me as I was lost and living all alone.

I am happy to report I am not lonely anymore, and I know as soon as you lay eyes on me it will be instant love as I am such a good looking fellow. I am a pyrenees retriever mix, and I know that is where I get my golden flowing locks from.

I have been working on my crate training and I understand how important this is so I am getting much more comfortable resting inside. I am fully house trained and love leash walks. I do get pretty excited when I see a car or other dogs and like to ‘woof’ at them. I am working on controlling my enthusiasm, but I will need your continued support. I know sit, leave it, and shake, and these are great skills to have.

I have not been around a lot of cats or dogs with my foster family, but I am told I did good with my first introduction. I really enjoy treats, a good bone and walks with you. I like being with humans so much, I do find I get nervous when I am alone. 

My foster describes me as loyal, loving, and energetic! What a great combination for a fellow as good looking as I am. Do you think you're the right home for a boy like me?

PLEASE NOTE: Because we do not have a public shelter, an adoption application must be filled out in order to be approved to meet any of our animals available for adoption. No exceptions. Serious inquiries only.

animal.description: Meet Darla!  She is timid, but really sweet.  She needs a patient owner.  Darla lived for her first 4 yrs in an outdoor kennel, and had not been on a leash her whole life.  We sent her to a trainer who got her leash ready for us in two weeks.  She has a brother, Charlie, that is still learning how to not balk and walk on a leash.  She was not abused, but more of a situation where she did not get the socialization she wanted.  Yet, the more time she spends at our center with our volunteers, she is wagging her tail and happy to see everyone.  A fenced yard would be ideal, as new sounds are somewhat scary to her.  She likes other dogs and would do really well with a confident dog that can show her, "how to be a dog and enjoy things".  She has lots of potential to overcome her fear and be a great companion dog.

animal.description:
***COVID 19 NOVEMBER 2020 PROTOCOL***

Due to the surge of Covid 19 and statewide restrictions, we are adopting to LOCAL (CLALLAM AND JEFFERSON COUNTY) RESIDENTS ONLY. We are not doing adoptions to Canada at this time due to the border closure. We do not ship animals.

OPHS is appointment only. All potential adopters must fill out an adoption application prior to setting up an appointment to meet the animal. An application can be found on our website https://www.ophumanesociety.org/dog-adoption-application

We have limited staff during this time, please allow 3-5 business days for us to process your application. We are screening the applications for the first BEST fit for each animal.

If you are approved, you will be contacted by us via phone or email to schedule an appointment.

NAME: Estelle
AGE: About 4 years old
WEIGHT: 6.8lbs
BREED(S):  Chihuahua
REASON FOR ARRIVAL:  Transfer from CA

GENERAL INFO ABOUT PERSONALITY: Estelle is as sweet as can be and is an absolute cuddle bug! She enjoys wearing warm sweaters when it is cold outside and she adores getting her belly rubbed. She will take short walks on a leash but also just loves being in your arms.

Estelle loves being around people and is so full of love to give. Sometimes when she sees someone about to go in her kennel she lets out an excited squeak! 

Estelle is small and delicate like a cute little mouse, so around other dogs she is pretty insecure. She can be a bit grumpy with other dogs so she would definitely be happiest as the only spoiled dog in the house. 

Activity Level? Low
Training Needs? Low
House Trained? Most likely
Leash Trained? Yes
Comfortable with kids? Unknown
Comfortable with strangers? A little shy at first
History with other dogs? Not so good.
History with cats? Good fit

Additional MEDICAL notes: None
Additional BEHAVIOR notes: Has had chronic ear infections which will need to be managed.

Animal Profile: Nala is an adorable 7 month old Shepherd/Husky mix who joined us from California on January 17th. She is a happy, smiley girl with a soft body. We will post more info as we get to know her.

Seattle Foster Update:
Nala is doing pretty well!! She is very nervous around strangers and other dogs, but when introduced slowly, she does alright. She gets overwhelmed easily and is slow to trust, but once she does trust you, she's very cute and fun. She's sweet as can be, but is still learning how to play and do normal dog things. She could benefit from having a resident dog to show her the ropes, but would do best with a calm, confident dog. Nala does well in the crate and in the car and has done well being left home in her crate.

Nala is looking for a home that will help her gain some confidence, hopefully with another confident calm dog to teach her the rope and no small children. We think she would benefit from a quiet home and she isn't a downtown kind of girl.

Adoption Info: Adoption fee is $500, which includes spay/neuter, current rabies/DAPPV/bordetella vaccinations, microchip, health certificate, and heartworm test. All adoption fees are donations to a Washington non-profit corporation and all donations go to benefit the animals in our rescue.

Apply online at www.DogGoneSeattle.org

Requirements: None

Preferred: Only Pet | Fenced Yard

Hi! I am Sophia Sue, and I'm just about the most cuddly girl you could ever imagine! I'm considered special needs because I am deaf, but don't let that scare you. I am working really hard on learning hand signals for my commands. Right now we are working on sit and come. I'm also learning how to use a light marker to indicate when I'm doing things right! Good thing I like treats because they really help with my training. I will need a patient, loving family to help me until I get all this training stuff down. I'll return your love with lots of love of my own, snuggles, and kisses!

I am potty trained and walk pretty nicely on a leash. I am working on crate training and learning to relax when I'm not in your sight. I promise I'm working hard at this, and giving me stuffed kongs really helps!

I love to play (when I'm not sleeping) so I will definitely need exercise and mental enrichment. I love the kids I have met so far, though I haven't met any little little ones yet. At the moment, I can play a little roughly with the cats. Training may help, but for now I prefer a home without any feline siblings! I have made some dog friends but would also prefer to be the only dog in the home for now. I also think a fenced in yard would be helpful for my safety, but it’s not required.

Please remember us deaf girls may take a bit to train but remember this. The ONLY THING a deaf dog CANNOT DO is hear.

Do you think I might be the cuddle buddy that you need? Apply today!

animal.description:
Meet Rylee!

Hello, my name is Rylee. I'm about 7 years old and weigh about 70 pounds. I had a home for my whole life, and they were very sad they had to let me go, but they knew I deserved better, so they surrendered me knowing I would find my perfect home. Im still a bit sad as well, but I'm sure once I find my new, forever home, that will help me feel a bit better. I lived with another dog in my last home, so it would be okay if I lived with another low-key, calm dog or two, who isn't in my face and can take cues from me when I tell them I'm not comfortable. I would do okay with teen-aged kids as well, but just like the dogs I could live with, they must be low-key and calm. I also think it's really fun to chase the cats out of the back yard at my foster home, so I shouldn't live with any. I'm completely house trained and am respectful of my home, so although I'm crate trained, foster mom says I don't have to be in one.

Listen, I really like to be around my humans, and maybe some of that is because I don't want to be left again, but I handle being alone pretty well if you need to go to work, or to the store. Foster mom says I'm down to earth, well behaved and loyal. I'd love to go in walks with you in the neighborhood so I can stay in shape, but I'm just as happy cuddling on the couch. I have some allergies, but they are easily managed and I get a bi-weekly bath, which I tolerate, as long as I get to snuggle with you afterwards. We could use that time to look deep into each other's eyes and learn all about each other! 

Albert's Dog Lounge is a transporting dog rescue, meaning that we rescue many of our dogs from high kill shelters in areas of dog overpopulation. We are a specialty rescue focusing primarily on senior and special needs dogs.  The vast majority of our dogs come from the Houston, TX area where we have an entire team of volunteers, coordinators, and fosters. We do also work with local shelters, rescues, and owners.  If you apply for a dog that is currently in our local Houston program, we will work to get your dog transported to WI as quickly as possible. We ask that you have patience during this time of uncertainty and unprecedented dog adoptions nationwide. 

Learn more about Albert's Dog Lounge, our mission, and adoption policies by visiting Albertsdoglounge.org. 

Our process includes an approved application, reference checks, a homevisit, and then a meet and greet with the dog. Adoption fee is $275.

Begin your application process by copying this link into your web browser: https://www.albertsdoglounge.org/apply

WI Dept. Of Agriculture License Number: 474085-DS

animal.description:
I am a male Yorkie mix.  I am about 6 years old and weigh about 9 lbs.  I am neutered, heartworm treated, current on shots, micro-chipped and on flea/heartworm prevention.  I have also had a negative fecal.  My adoption is $300.

I was found as a stray and no one claimed me.  Unfortunately, I tested positive for heartworms but luckily, the rescue has treated me.   I will need to be retested in April 2021.  If still positive, which should be unlikely, the rescue will have their vet continue with any care for the heartworms.  Therefore, I must be adopted locally to the Altamonte Springs/Orlando area.  I also have a sensitive stomach and need to eat a particular food or else I will get an upset tummy.

I am a sweet boy, most of the time.  However, I do have an attitude.  I will guard my possessions and will bite if I don't want you to take it.  Also, I will tolerate being brushed/groomed but once I am done, I am done.  If you do not heed my warning, I will bite.  I am also pushy/bossy with other dogs.

I need an adopter that is experienced with small dog aggression.  I would make a great companion for the right person.

Please email for an adoption application.  Once the application is approved, we will arrange for you to meet and adopt. 

We do not adopt out of state.
Due to many bounced checks, we now require that adoption donations be cash only.  However, if you make a general donation to the organization (not associated with the adoption of a pet) we do accept checks and paypal.  If you are unable to adopt right now, won't you please make a donation to help care for the pets?  THANK YOU!!

animal.description:
We are looking for a foster-to-adopt home for this beautiful boy.

Mikka is a gorgeous, highly intelligent 8-year old black shepherd looking for a special home.  Mikka did not receive adequate socialization in his previous life, so he is now learning what is expected of him. Given the time to learn and observe, Mikka is blossoming.  He is slowly getting used to having more freedom than he has been used to, and is enjoying the gradual approach. He is making new human friends at the shelter and is ready to be in a home. Although initially fearful/anxious, Mikka appears to be able to quickly form positive relationships with familiar and unfamiliar people with proper introductions. Mikka is a large dog and has hyperextension in both front and back legs.  His new home will ideally provide soft bedding and keep his weight on the lower side due to arthritis.  He will need a dog saavy and patient family, ideally with German Shepherd experience, to be successful.  In particular, his family needs to be willing and able to establish routines, and keep a keen eye on how Mikka responds to everything in life.

Mikka doesn’t enjoy car rides.  His activity level is low to moderate.  He is sweet, sensitive, curious, and he is learning to be silly.  He is enjoying learning about clicker training.

Mikka was assessed by a behavioral veterinarian, who provided these recommendations:
•	Quiet, adult only home 
•	Slow, gradual introductions with new people and environments.  It will be important to give Mikka time needed when acclimating in a new environment and towards new people.
•	Other animals possible although caution and slow introductions are needed.  He doesn’t have a lot of experience with other dogs, so for now at least, he needs to be the only dog in a home.  We are unsure about cats.
•	Positive reinforcement training for clear communication and behavior modification 

We believe that Mikka will be a spectacular companion, given the right home and circumstances.  

PLEASE NOTE - We will check your veterinary reference, to ensure that current and prior pets have a history of being kept up to date on vaccines, annual exams and recommended bloodwork. We also do home checks to make sure that your home environment meets the needs of the particular animal you are interested in.

If you’re interested in adoption, please fill out our online adoption survey at https://www.olddogsnewdigs.com/adoption-survey/. We are partnering with PAWS Brave Hearts in Calais to find the right home for Mikka.  You can contact them by email: info@pawsbravehearts.org or phone:  207-4547662.

animal.description:
Just like the Vanda orchid, our girl Vanda is gorgeous. This all white beauty has the cutest black mask around her eyes and one black spot at the top of her tail. Don't let her mask fool you, Vanda has nothing to hide. She's housebroken and loves all people as well as all the doggos - she'd even love to have her very own doggie siblings! Vanda attends daycare and she is every dog's favorite playmate. She's energetic, loving all things hiking, running around, and playing (she ADORES toys), and she loves going on car rides. At the end of her busy day, Vanda loves to curl up with her people and dream of tomorrow's adventures. Apply for Vanda and fulfill her dream of a furever home of her own.

Vanda is under 2 years old and weighs about 55 pounds.

If you're interested in meeting Vanda, please visit our website to learn about our adoption process and to fill out an application, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

All of our dogs and cats will be micro-chipped, spayed or neutered, and up-to-date on vaccinations at the time of adoption. For more photos of Vanda, follow us on Facebook Gateway Pet Guardians and Instagram @gatewaypets ... #gpgvanda.

To view other adoptable pets from our shelter, please visit, www.gatewaypets.org/adopt

Gateway Pet Guardians is proud to offer a variety of mixed breed dogs available for adoption. However, please keep in mind that we rarely know the genetic background of the animals we rescue and, as such, we cannot guarantee the exact breed combinations found within this dog. However, we do not know his/her actual genetic makeup. Just know that this dog is probably a variety of several different breeds that have combined to create one very amazing and unique animal.

animal.description:
Casper is a big ol ham! He is Heartworm postive and going through treatment currently and will for months ahead. Please look into heartworm treatment in dogs before applying. We have a few options for adoption for him as he has a lengthly treatment plan which requires much work on any new adoptors part, luckily he is non symptomatic and able to have a somewhat active lifestyle while in treatment but, is not out of the woods yet.

 He also has some behavior hiccups that he is also working through, but he is so willing to learn he is flying through his training! He is looking for a home with a strong GSD background and very knowledgeable of the breed that will be able to have training classes with a professional set up after adoption so he can continue his progress! He gets along great with other dogs and when it comes to cats hes a big scared baby if they swat at him. He loves to snuggle and be as close to his person as he can! He is currently in a foster and attends doggy darcare everyday and gets glowing reviews!

Casper would require a 6 ft fenced in yard

IF you are Casper's perfect match let us know! Please head on over to all4animalsrescue.org and fill out an application and we can set up a time for you to meet!

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Arlo (TX) is a male mixed breed pup rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Arlo is 9 months old at the time of intake in January 2021. Arlo is good with people and other dogs. This poor little guy was hit by a car, sustaining several fractures. Rather than provide the medical care Arlo required as a result of his injuries, his owner opted to euthanize him. That's when Rescue Dogs Rock NYC stepped in and said NO WAY! Arlo is an adorable, sweet pup who doesn't deserve to die, so we took him in and he has now received the surgery he required to put his leg back together. Arlo is now looking for a new home. If you would like to be Arlo's forever family, please apply online to adopt Arlo (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Beignet (TX) is a female Australian Shepherd/Great Pyrenees mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Beignet is 4 weeks old at the time of intake in January 2021. Beignet is good with people of all ages and other dogs. Beignet is a beautiful, sweet pup who is very lucky to be alive. She was found clinging to her lifeless Momma on the side of the road where her Momma landed after having been hit by a car. Beignet is just a baby and could not have survived on her own. Fortunately, an Animal Control Officer picked Beignet up, and rather than take her to the kill shelter where her life would have come to end because she needed to be bottle fed, the Animal Control Officer diverted Beignet to rescue. And now Beignet is not only being bottle fed, but she will be given a fabulous future in a wonderful forever home. If you are looking for a playful, happy, gorgeous four legged pup, Beignet is your girl! Please apply online to adopt Beignet (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Sandy Claws! I'm part of the Nightmare Before Christmas litter. My mom is Sahara, a 50 lb retriever mix. We have no idea who my dad is, but he was probably pretty big. Foster mom thinks I'll be around 70 lbs fully grown. She calls me her little miss independent because I like to do things my own way. At only 2 weeks old, I was already climbing out of the whelping bed so I could sleep away from my siblings. Like my mom, I'm fearless, headstrong, affectionate, and extremely playful. You can also watch for stories, pictures, and videos about me on JR's Pups-N-Stuff's Facebook page https://www.facebook.com/groups/40103261297/. Ask to meet me today!!
 
Adoption fee: $475

Adoption fees for all dogs/puppies include a $50 refundable training deposit. Complete your basic training program and provide a copy of the certificate within 4 months (120 days) of adoption and we will refund $50 of the original adoption fee.
 
All dogs/puppies have been fully vetted including spay/neuter, micro-chipping, worming, heartworm testing and preventative treatment, flea/tick preventative, and all required age appropriate vaccinations. As required by Wisconsin Act 90, all dogs will have received a veterinarian exam (CVI) within the past 30 days.
 
Our adoption process requires the submission of an application. Applications and Adoption Rules can be found on our website, on the "HOW TO ADOPT" tab at JRsPupsNStuff.org. Upon receipt of the completed application, we will process the application including: contact with your veterinarian and completion of a home visit. Please be sure to include the contact information for your vet as we will call. If your vet requires an information release, please be sure to contact them as soon as you submit your application. We are a group of volunteers with families and jobs, so please be patient and allow a few days for our response.
 
JR's Pups-N-Stuff Dog Sellers License 270089-DS

animal.description:
Lacey was transferred to Valley Humane on 12/31 along with her 10 puppies from Stockton Animal Services. She had been surrendered by her owner. Lacey weighs 67 pounds and is estimated to be between 4 and 7 years old. Lacey has undergone a lot of major changes over the past few months including raising her puppies and recently being separated from them as they are adopted. She is looking for a very patient owner who can give her the time and space to further acclimate and adjust.

Lacey is an extremely smart dog, with the grace and body of a gazelle. She is gentle, very sweet, and people-oriented. Lacey is cautious initially but with lots of love, patience, and consistency will become more confident and comfortable, making her an amazing companion. In no time she'll be rolling over for tummy rubs, shaking hands with her graceful paws, and following you like a sleek shadow. 

It is incredibly helpful that Lacey knows her name and responds very well to it. She is very responsive to a calm voice and there is no need to ever yell or loudly correct her. This girl is built for running and galloping and loves chasing balls and squeaky toys. Lacey loves her toys and playing with her "person" outside or inside. She is well-behaved indoors, with no accidents. She is taken outside to go potty every few hours during the day but sleeps through the night. She loves going on long walks, but has limited experience on a leash and will require more practice with a patient and attentive walker. She currently puts herself to sleep in an extra-large wire crate in the same room with us. She can walk in and out of the crate and it provides her with her own private space. It has a large blanket draped over three sides and a soft dog bed and towels inside. 

Lacey should be placed with someone who is experienced with dogs and who can patiently and consistently work with her to bring out her confidence, silliness, and even more loving personality. She is very smart and learns quickly. She would do well in a calm household with people who are active and can spend time with her outdoors playing and enjoying long walks or hikes.

This dog is currently being treated for an ear infection in both ears. When she arrived at VHS, she had evidence of chronic ear infections that were previously untreated (especially in the right ear). Due to the chronicity and lack of previous treatment, the right ear pinna is thickened and no longer stands upright. Ear infections are common in dogs. They are not contagious to humans or to other dogs. This dog appears to be prone to ear infections and may develop them frequently through out her lifetime, requiring treatment by a veterinarian and regular care by her adoptive family. A long acting ear treatment was placed into both ears on 1/7/21 and repeated on 1/22/21. The adopting family must be willing to seek appropriate follow-up veterinary care by their veterinarian. If her right ear does not respond to appropriate therapy, the adopting family's veterinarian may recommend a consultation for a possible surgical intervention. Any further medical expenses sought out after adoption will be at the cost of the adopter.

During shelter-in-place, Valley Humane is conducting adoptions by appointment only. If you would like to adopt Crescent, please complete an Adoption Inquiry Form (copy and paste the following URL into your browser), https://valleyhumane.org/adoption/adoption-inquiry-form/

An adoption counselor will reach out via telephone to conduct an adoption interview. Once you have submitted your application, stand by to answer our call! Animals posted to the website are ready to go home and applicants are typically called the same day as the Inquiry Form is received.

If approved, we will schedule an adoption appointment for you, your family and the animal at our facility in Pleasanton.

https://valleyhumane.org/safe-adoption-guidelines/

animal.description:
Earl is the sweet old soul his name suggests. Hes a very easy going boy and once he gains trust, he gets along with everyone. He seems to be house trained and loves a comfy spot to take a nap. He really enjoys walks and is great on the leash. He doesnt know any commands but is very food motivated and picked up sit in just a few days. He is still unsure and timid with new situations/people/dogs/noises but he gains confidence each day. Once he is comfortable he is playful and has a puppy like curiosity. He is such a wonderful, handsome boy! Shy at first, but with tasty food, a comfy place to lay and some tlc he will settle right in.

HW+ simply means the dog has tested positive for heart worms in our screening process. We utilize what is called the fast-kill method which means we place the dog on antibiotics for 30 days and then administer 3 injections in increments afterward. The cost to treat heart worms is rather steep. However, thanks to our generous donors, we are able to cover that cost for our adopters so long as they go to our veterinarian, Red Rocks Animal Center in Lakewood.

animal.description:
Hi, my name is Hermoine (I go by Hermie). I like cold nights by the fire, a warm fluffy blanket, morning belly rubs, scooby snacks, squeaky toys, big ole bones and going on walks/jogs with my person. Favorite times of the day are breakfast and dinner. Nothing better than a great meal and a nice nap afterward.

Im pretty much potty trained, and I know how to sit like a lady. Im 3-years-old and about 27 pounds - just right for my height and body type. While Im mostly a house-dog, I like my time outdoors as well. I rarely bark when outdoors and enjoy watching the squirrels run across the fence. I never dig as it gets my nails dirty. One of my favorite things is walking/jogging in the neighborhood. Neighbors marvel at my leash skills.

So everyone has a story. Mine isnt so great. I was rescued from a pretty bad situation with two other dogs. We obviously weren't Weimaraners but WRT couldn't just leave us in the situation we were in (there are several pictures posted here of my "before" look). WRT DNA tested us and I'm 37.5% Beagle, 25% Labrador, 12.5% Amstaff, and 25% Sporting Breed group. We all had a variety of worms (including heart worms) and mange. So, Imwell, Im bald. Im getting some hair now, but it seems to take FOREVER to grow back. But for a bald girl, Im pretty cute!

It takes time for me to trust people. But I definitely bonded with my foster mom. She has another dog a beagle/basset. Im not very good with sharing, and would really prefer to be an only dog. Her dog is friendly enough, but it seems like every time her dog wants something, I want it too. Envy is one of the seven deadly sinsthats what my foster mom says. Anyway, I want to be specialan only dog.

While Im guilty of getting into occasional tussles with my foster brother, I NEVER bite. Thats just not my thing. Panic maybe, bitenever. So Im looking for that special person with patience and kindness, someone that lets me lick the plate every now and then . I hope thats you!

I'm being fostered in the San Antonio area if you'd like to meet me.

animal.description:
This boy is a lover! His foster mom says he is such a great doggie - he is gentle with her many cats,quickly made friends with her other dogs, plays with her pre-teen son, and is a world class snuggler. Goofy and a fun boy to have around. Smart too! Bart learned to sit patiently while his breakfast and dinner are being prepared and to wait for mom's que to begin eating. At 4-5 months old and 40 lbs, Bart is going to be large as adult. Guesses on his breed include Border Collie / Anatolian Shepherd / Great Pyr/ maybe a little American Staffordshire Terrier? He is on his way to being housetrained and already sleeps contently through the night in his crate. Sweet boy!!

The vet said that given Bart's larger size it is important for him to not jump in and out of vehicles or other high objects. The rescue will be providing a loading ramp for him to make car rides easier.

If you are interested in meeting Bart please complete an application at https://www.circle2rescue.com/dog-adoption-application/ The adoption fee of $300 includes spay/neuter, vaccinations, microchip and dewormer.

Please note, Circle 2 Rescue cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have limited history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

animal.description:
Auguste came to the rescue way too thin, almost hairless, heartworm positive and overall defeated. Fast forward just a few months and he's in great health, has a beautiful grey coat and is loving life! Auguste adores the children he lives with, doesn't bother the cats and plays nicely with other dogs. He's house, crate and leash trained, does well in the bath and the car and is all around pretty "low maintenance". He is also very eager to please his people (and very treat motivated). This very handsome good boy may be older but he is full of tail wags, cuddles and has plenty of life left to live with his forever family. Auguste is up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, neutered, and microchipped. His adoption fee is $175.
All of our dogs are spayed or neutered, up to date on age appropriate vaccinations, microchipped and if over 6 months of age, heartworm tested and on heartworm preventative in their foster home.

We require an approved application to meet any of our dogs. We do not have a shelter location and will not arrange a meeting without an approved application.

We strive to make sure the bios provided for our dogs are complete and accurate; we do understand that mistakes happen, however, so if you absolutely cannot find the answer to your question in the dog's bio, you can contact us for more information.

We require a home visit for each dog we adopt out, so we adopt within a 2 hour radius of Dayton, OH. If you are outside of this radius, we encourage you to contact your local rescue or shelter.

animal.description:
Are you looking for a low-maintenance, go with the flow, kind of girl? The kind who loves ear scratches and short walks? Margo is your gal!

Margo is a sweet, gentle lab mix, a small town girl who once roamed her hometown, visiting the local grocery store where the employees fed her before finding herself at an animal shelter and finally to Muddy Paws.

Margo is excellent with cats, dogs and children. Though she is sweet and cuddly, she walks well on a leash, has plenty of pep in her step and loves car rides! Margo had surgery to remove benign mammary tumors and a cyst from her neck and is healing well. Margo is the sweetest girl and needs a great home to give her lots of love for her remaining years.

The suggested adoption donation for Margo is $250. We are a 501c3 organization which means that your donation may be TAX DEDUCTIBLE. Your donation goes toward the high cost of veterinary care for our animals in rescue, as well as providing supportive services to animals in homes.

Information about the adoption process: All adoptions require a completed ADOPTION APPLICATION. Once your application is approved, we will put you in touch with the dogs foster to see if you and the pet are a good match. If so, we will arrange a meeting for you and the pet. The adoptions for all of our animals will take place in the Omaha, NE area and must be done by the adoptive family in person. We do not ship or deliver.

Please Note: We are a RESCUE, which is different from a shelter. We conduct veterinary and personal reference checks during the application approval process. We always select the right applicant for each dog, based on the dogs needs. If you and the dog are not a good match, we will help you select another dog, or we will keep your approved application on file for 6 months.

To learn about Muddy Paws Second Chance Rescue or donate to our animals, please visit our website at MuddyPawsSecondChanceRescue.com or our Facebook Page.

animal.description:
Personality: Beckett is an athletic, energetic dog who is looking for a dog savvy home that is just as athletic as he is. He can be a little tentative in new places and can be sensitive to invasive handling, but with some time and space to settle in, he warms up quickly. His future family should be familiar with dog body language and reading his signals to help him slowly build confidence. He loves to have access to a yard where he gets more space to meet people, but he likes long walks, runs, and hikes even better! He would do best in an adult household with experience around working breeds like him. 

History: Beckett came to HSSV as a stray.

Dog/Cat Skills: Beckett has participated in dog playgroup, and can be forward in greets. He has shown to be tentative with and possibly target intact/recently neutered male dogs (not uncommon as he was only recently neutered as well). Beckett does best with social, playful females who tolerate his forward approach. He will play chase and enjoys running around the yard with dogs. He has shown hyper focus on cats and willingness to chase them. Adopters should be familiar with breed tendencies. 

Leash Skills: Beckett can pull on leash, but needs time to get comfortable before being harnessed. He walks okay on leash once he can get some energy out. Beckett is eager to meet dogs, and can become excited and vocal when he sees them. We are working on this by redirecting him with treats and happy talk. 

Ready to meet Beckett? Fill out the form to request an appointment Primary Color: Tri Color Weight: 53lbs Age: 2yrs 0mths 2wks Animal has been Neutered

Diamond is a high energy girl who will need an active home to get her energy out. She will need structure to continue working on her manners, but she is funny and loves people.

She does best on chicken-free food as it appeared to cause skin irritation.

animal.description:
Angela is an adorable 7-year-old female Shih Tzu that weighs 9 pounds. She is a sweet gal that loves to lounge outside in the sunshine, curl up next to her person for snuggle time, and enjoys the company of other dogs. Angela is doing great with potty training and we are confident she will do well with a consistent routine. She is laid back, friendly, and super sweet! She had to be shaved due to heavy matting, but we know her fur will grow back and be beautiful once again soon. Sadly, Angela is heartworm positive and currently undergoing the slow kill method with oral medication. Our rescue will provide the medication needed for 12 months. She is spayed, vaccinated, fecal negative, and microchipped, She is $350 plus TX sales tax with an approved application: www.recycledpomsbcs.com/adopt

Texas law requires that all humane organizations (Rescues, SPCA's, Humane Societies, State nonprofit, and charitable 501c3 exempt orgs) collect and remit sales and use tax to the Texas Comptroller on their adoption fees.

We do not ship or transport our dogs. We require all adopters to meet the dog in person to ensure it is a good fit. We represent the dog to the best of our ability and since they are in rescue, we do not always get their history.

Please note: We are a non-profit Pomeranian Rescue with dogs in private foster homes. We do not have a facility open to the public. We require an approved application before a potential adopter is introduced to a dog. We contact vet references to ensure animals in the home are current on vaccinations, heart worm prevention, and sterilization. We do not adopt our dogs to homes in which an animal is not spayed or neutered. A home visit may be required.

Please visit our website for more information and an adoption application. www.recycledpomsbcs.com

animal.description:
Camilla was rescued from Korea!

Since she was rescued overseas, adoption donations will include the expenses incurred, such as international travel costs, etc. estimated around $1200.


She has been a hilarious delight since she stepped off the plane.


She is loving and spirited. Despite the language barrier, she can sit for treats! She is a playful girl who would do well in a home with a play-partner-in-residence. The dog sibling should be her emotional equal - Camilla can been bossy and possessive with your affection.


She  is cuddly with people and pups. She loves to bomb around a park with a  soccer ball or similar-sized ball.  Beware anyone with a chuck-it!  She will leap to grab it, she is obsessed with them! She will not be denied- she jumps well! 


She walks well on leash. She is learning manners everyday and is a good student. She very much wants to please. A tired Camilla is a  better roommate - in her foster home she gets 3-4 good plays and romps a  day.


Her history is that she has terrible separation anxiety and is willful. She  has quickly relaxed and enjoyed the routine and residents in her foster  home. She is potty trained and respectfully sleeps at the foot of the bed!


She  is most potty trained, but expect an adjustment period that should pass  quickly.   She should be taken right outside in the morning and don't  let her save her poop for inside!  She likes to poop off-leash.
IF INTERESTED, PLEASE FILL OUT AN ADOPTION APPLICATION ON OUR WEBSITE: https://www.wonderdogrescue.org/adoption-application

As  for eating, like with most dogs, everyone should have good space  around their food bowl. AND  longer lasting chewies/bones should be  carefully managed to maintain harmony between residents!

SHE LOVES HOSES and baths.


She  will start sleeping by your head....but when she feels secure - will  move to the foot of the bed or to your side.  She is not great in the  car - she wants to be in your lap - so need to secure her in the back  seat with a leash.


Her foster has not used a crate with her. It hasn't been necessary.

animal.description:
Its sweet momma Tallulah's turn to find her happily ever after. She is almost 2 years old, and likely a boxer, pittie and shepherd mix of sorts. This endearing momma
was picked up off the streets while being very pregnant on November 17th of 2020. She was rescued from the shelter on Thanksgiving day and two days later she gave birth to 10 puppies, all who have been adopted now! With having no knowledge of her true background, her foster family showered Tallulah with love and grace. For the birth of her babies, foster mom and her two daughters helped to midwife Tallulah which secured her trust in people. Over the past 8 weeks, Tallulah has gone from scared and not knowing hardly anything about being in a house, to knowing the love that is shared in a home. Her foster mom truly believes that Tallulah has learned a great deal from having a calm and confident alpha in the house and she is so thankful for love and fun! Tallulah is 75% lover of cough snuggles and cheese, 25% lover of outside play and runs. She is great with other dogs and with children. She is a shoe thief, so keep a look out. She has never destroyed a pair, but her foster family does make sure to put them away in the closet. She is house trained for the most part. If you go past 10 hours over night she *may have an accident. This has happened maybe twice in the past month. She truly sees no value in the command "sit" but is 100% spot on with "come" and "leave it." She does well with boundaries. She is happiest outside running and playing with our other dogs and children. Of note, she does like to nibble at times when really playing, so for that reason, we feel she would not do well with small children as that might scare them. Tallulah is a sweet girl with a lot of love and fun to offer her furever family. Send your application in today at www.underhoundrailroad.org.

Tallulah is currently being fostered in North Carolina and may transport North to her furever home.

Thibodeaux cheated death twice that day as when Thibodeaux was picked up by Animal Control, the Animal Control Officer diverted him to rescue rather than bringing Thibodeaux to the shelter where his life would likely have ended upon arrival. Thibodeaux is being bottle fed and well cared for in his foster home, but he is looking forward to the new happy, safe life we promised him in his very own forever home. animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.My name is Milo and I'm a 10 month old male GSD who is ready to spend the rest of my years playing and snuggling as much as possible!

I am fully house-trained and will bark and let you know when I really have to go. I am also fully crate trained and don't mind being in the crate for several hours at a time throughout the day. I'm not at all food driven, I just want all of the love you will give me.

I know most of the basic commands (sit, lay down) but am still working on impulse control and staying in one place. I love to be around people I know and even love to meet new people. Sometimes I scare people with my bark when we first meet, but I warm up to people really quickly. I have played with many different dogs with no problems but I'm still a puppy, so sometimes I can be a little too much for older dogs. I do really well with playing with only the toys that I know are ok for me to play with and I love when I can chew on bones.

I get around really well with three legs (please scroll through the pictures of my bio to read through my journey!) and am working on learning how to run. Don't worry, when I see a squirrel, I can pick up and GO! I need a little more down time, but I'm almost ready to start going on walks. I haven't tried stairs just yet since I've been healing from my surgery, but my foster mom is sure I would do great with a little assistance and training. (Please note that at some point in the future I may need to have a hip replacement. At this point in time we aren't sure of if or when it would be needed).

I would do really well in a house where my parents will continue my training. My foster mom says I can be a little stubborn--I like to talk back when I'm frustrated or when she won't let me do something I want to do. I love kids and am very gentle but I am still working on not being so mouthy. I love to learn new things and just like many GSDs, I like to be wherever my people are. My foster mom says she can't wait to find me a home that I can call my own because she knows I will make someone a perfect companion!

I am being fostered near Charlotte, NC.

If you are interested in adopting me, please reach out to your adoption coordinator. If you do not have an adoption coordinator, please fill out an adoption application at https://freedomgermanshepherdrescue.org

She has been doing great with "Sit" and she is learning "Stay", "Come", "Lay" (to lay down), "Over here", and of course her name.

Her foster mama is taking good care of her and has shared these updates: She has been out for walks with me carrying her until she gets fully vaccinated so she has been able to get some fresh air and outside time. She barks when she meets new people and quiets down once she smells them and enjoys interacting with them. She does fantastic in the car. She is full of energy when initially in the car and settles down to sleep when the car starts moving. She has learned to cuddle and loves it. She has exhibited some separation anxiety but it is helped with the treat toys.

If you live in the San Diego or surrounding areas and think Pepper will be a good addition to your family please inquire to receive an application.

We don’t know Liam’s exact age but we estimate he is about 5-6 years older. Liam is a gentle, sweet boy looking to leave his old life behind. He has done well meeting other dogs. Liam walks well on leash but doesn’t know any commands. Liam hasn’t been around children but we think he’d be good with older children. Liam rides well in the car and has no issues with handling. We are excited for this sweet boy to start his new life and we know he’ll continue to come out of his shell.

If interested in adopting, apply at www.gsrescue1.org. An application is the first step in our process. We only adopt local to Chicagoland.

animal.description:
I am a female chocolate lab.  I was born on 1/27/18 and I weigh 65 lbs.  I am spayed, heartworm negative, current on shots, micro-chipped and on flea/heartworm prevention.  My adoption is $400.

I was given up by my owners because I was being kept outside in the yard and I can escape if left alone.  I can also be a bit shy with new people or settings.  I am crate trained and do well going on walks.

When I first came into rescue, I had a tick borne illness called Ehrlichiosis that makes it hard for my blood to clot.  However, I have been treated and retested and I am now negative.

Please email for an adoption application.  Once the application is approved, we will arrange for you to meet and adopt. 

We do not adopt out of state.
Due to many bounced checks, we now require that adoption donations be cash only.  However, if you make a general donation to the organization (not associated with the adoption of a pet) we do accept checks and paypal.  If you are unable to adopt right now, won't you please make a donation to help care for the pets?  THANK YOU!!

animal.description:
****PETronus Rescue endeavors to include all pertinent information for each of the dogs within our organization with regard to approximate age, potty training status, kennel training status, temperament, activity level, dog/cat friendliness, etc in an effort to give those considering adopting as much information as we have.  Inquiries requesting additional information will not be returned, due to limited volunteers. Thank you for your understanding ****

Meet Chucky.

Chucky is being returned to our rescue, along with his sister Annabelle, due to their family being relocated to Australia for work.

He is estimated to have been born in June 2019, making him just over 1.5 years old. He is house broken, walks well on a leash, has moved past the chewing stage for the most part, is up to date on his vaccinations, spayed, microchipped, and is good with all people and other dogs.

He had not been cat tested.

—————————————

All PETronus Rescue dogs receive basic vaccinations (distemper/parvo, bordetella, & rabies), spay/ neuter, and microchip prior to adoption. We also treat any know medical issues, including heartworms.

Our dogs live in foster homes while they wait patiently for their forever families to find them. This is beneficial in that they learn house manners, crate training, housebreaking, etc while they wait and we are also able to get a very realistic picture of their energy level, temperament, etc so that we can place them in a home that is the best fit.

Our adoption fees are $200 for dogs over 1 year of age and $250 for dogs under 1 year of age. Puppies receive 3 rounds of puppy vaccinations.

If you are interested in adopting one of our amazing dogs, please fill out our adoption application here http://bit.ly/PRAdoption and we will be in touch!

animal.description: Theo was an owner surrender, due to no fault of his own. He was abandoned there when they moved in so they took him in. He is all terrier when it comes to kids and would do best in a home with older kids or no kids. They weren't sure how he was with other dogs or cats, he seems to be intimidated by other dogs when passing his cage. He does take some time to warm up to people and will growl and even snap at strangers if he feels scared, sometimes unpredictable. He is very food motivated and would do best in a house hold with someone who has time to work him through his guarding issues. He loves going on long walks and playing with squeaky toys or playing fetch. We feel like he would prefer to be the only pet, in a child free home where he can receive all the attention and one on one time, with a quiet house hold. He does know how to sit and walks well on a leash.

READ THE FOLLOWING FOR INSTRUCTIONS ON SUBMITTING AN APPLICATION AND FOR A DESCRIPTION  OF THIS PET:

Meet Momma Callie! Callie is a 30lb, approximately 2 year old slightly shy at first sweetheart.  She had suffered a gunshot wound to her shoulder at some point, the shrapnel shows up on xray, but she still uses that leg with ease and is really fast on it to boot!  Callie is good with other dogs and doesn't mind cats at all.  She is still relearning how to go to the bathroom outside but will use pee pads indoors.  I don't think she is a fan of the cold and loves to cuddle! Callie would make a great candidate for city living and/or apartment dwellers.

Callie is up to date on vaccines, spayed, microchipped, dewormed, and treated with flea/tick/hw preventative.  Her adoption fee is $375.00.

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING, PLEASE READ THE FOLLOWING INSTRUCTIONS:

- The first step towards adoption is to complete an adoption application, which can be found online at our website www.roadtriprescues.com, under the “ADOPT” tab.

- Do not use the Petfinder links or email to ask us about our adoptable dog listings - we do not always receive these messages and will not respond to them.

- Please do not ask if a dog is still available - we do our best to update their status as quickly as possible.  If a dog is listed for adoption, it means we have not yet approved an adopter and are still accepting applications.

- PLEASE NOTE THAT ONLY APPROVED ADOPTERS WILL BE PERMITTED TO MEET OUR RESCUES - WE ARE A FOSTER BASED RESCUE AND ALL OF OUR DOGS LIVE WITH US AS FAMILY. 

Thanks for considering a rescue pup!

animal.description:
Angel is a 2yr old Chihuahua mix looking for her new forever home! Angel came to us after coming from horrible living conditions and not being cared for properly. She is 19.5lbs and is full grown. When she first came to us, she was very hesitant and wasn't sure if she liked us. After 2 days of giving her space and time, she opened up and became the most sweetest and silliest girl. Once she was comfortable, we learned that she loves to be with her people, loves to play with other dogs, loves to do zoomies, and loves to play with toys! She also loves treats, going outside to run and play, and napping with a canine companion. We recommend an adult home only, and how she is with men is unknown. It would be best for everyone living in the home to come meet her. Since she has been with us, she seems to be housebroken and kennel trained. In a new environment she may need a few patience and reminders though. Angel would do best in a home with a yard. She is doing okay with leash training but ideally would do best with a yard. She may also do best with a confident, friendly, playful canine companion that loves to play and loves to nap with their canine buddy. Angel is the sweetest, most forgiving, silly and playful girl that just didn't have the best start in her short life. She will take patience adjusting in her new home with her new people, but it is worth the wait we promise! Angel is spayed, up to date on vaccinations, vet checked, and microchipped. Her adoption fee is $280 and comes with a complimentary vet visit. To meet her, please bring the whole household 2 legged and 4 to ensure it is a good fit.
Please come to our shelter location at 1102 W. Hatcher Rd. Phoenix, AZ 85021 anytime during business hours. We are open Tuesday-Sunday from 11AM-6PM. --COVID update: To adhere to CDC guidelines, we are open for adoptions only at a max capacity of 10 people in the building at a time. Masks/face coverings are required. For the safety of our staff and customers, we ask that you practice social distancing, sanitization, and if exposed to Covid-19 or sick to please stay home.

animal.description:
We almost lost Ellie a bit ago-LOL-she blended right in to the dappled snow on the grass!!  At the time she may have wanted to be a little more incognito, she was settling in and really wanted to be left alone for a time. Ellia is 7 years old we are told, so that gives her a pretty good lifetime with a family. She seems to have been very much loved, and very well fed!! Sweet girl enjoys a fine meal, I can relate. That makes coming into the foster/rescue system a little more difficult. We could see her "people searching", a term used to describe a dog in rescue that is waiting for their family to return. She misses her family, sweet girl. 

The good news is that Ellie has the tools to acclimate. She knows what love is and is very accepting of new people, she is such a little doll. She has lived with other dogs and even cats and is a little lady of a dog. Ellie is soft and snuggly, not pushy at all, she is the type girl that will step away if another dog wants to hog the attention, just makes you want to reach out to that sweet little face even more!!!  However, Ellie does have "white coat syndrome", she does NOT like going to the veterinarian and will need to be muzzled. Some dogs will take a little doggy downer before that trip to help out with the nerves, not uncommon, and not a huge issue. 

Ellie will do well with a loving family, someone that will help her stay active and perhaps lose a couple pounds. She has had some chronic ear issues, perhaps a grain free/chicken free diet will help. We are doing that now and she seems to be doing well, we have noticed less redness around her eyes and ears. Sweet Ellie is 43 pounds, does fantastic with the other dogs, is a sweetheart of a girl and is looking for a family to love. Please--no long hours alone. Cattle dogs need activity and a job, she is not a couch potato type dog. 

Ellie's adoption fee is $300, which is tax deductible. She is fully vetted, spayed and chipped. She will come with plenty of supplies to help her settle into her new home as well as a free month of insurance if you would like. Please email Kristine at joysparrows@gmail.com.

animal.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
Roux (TX) is a male Australian Shepherd/Great Pyrenees mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Roux is 4 weeks old at the time of intake in January 2021. Roux is good with people of all ages and other dogs. Roux's life started out tragically, and it could have continued that way until it ended most likely before Roux was just a month old. Roux was found clinging to his Momma's dead body on the side of a road where she ended up when she was hit by a car. Rather than stop to help this Momma, the person who hit her just kept driving right past Momma and her babies. Roux was picked up by Animal Control and, since he required bottle feeding, his life would likely have ended upon arrival at the shelter. But this very kind Animal Control Officer diverted Roux to rescue and saved his life twice. Roux is now a Rescue Dogs Rock NYC pup, and his life is no longer tragic. In fact, his life is charmed! Roux is a happy go lucky, playful puppy. If you are looking for a four legged, active buddy, please apply online to adopt Roux (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.

animal.description:
QUEEN, shelter number D21-01002, is a female terrier mix. She is about three years old and weighs about 35 pounds. She was surrendered to the shelter by her owner along with SAGE; we are not sure why. She is quite friendly and has no obvious health or behavioral problems. She walks well on leash and enjoys being petted. She should be good with kids and with most other dogs. With any of our dogs, it’s a good idea for potential adopters with other dogs at home to bring them out to meet the potential adoptee dog before making a final decision.
QUEEN would make a great indoor/outdoor dog. She has short hair and will not tolerate cold weather very well. She should at least be allowed to sleep indoors and be brought in during cold, wet or stormy weather during the day if possible. She should have plenty of water and good shade if left outside in the summer. She would make a great companion for watching TV or just hanging out in the evenings and would love to be included in any family activities indoors or out whenever possible.
QUEEN is looking for another chance at a forever home.
Levelland Animal Control is understaffed right now and adoptions are by appointment only. If you would like to meet QUEEN for a possible adoption, please call (806) 891-0829 from 9 to 5; if (806) 891-0829 doesn’t answer, call (806) 894-6164 and tell them you are interested in adopting a dog. You may need to refer to QUEEN by her shelter number, D21-01002, when talking to an Animal Control employee.
Levelland Animal Control is understaffed right now and adoptions are by appointment only.
All our dogs are vaccinated for Parvo, distemper, Bordetella (kennel cough) and most other common dog diseases. We do not vaccinate them for Rabies. There is no adoption fee, but the adopter will be responsible for having the dog spayed or neutered and for the Rabies shot.
Check the Google map for directions to the shelter located at 109 Commerce in Levelland, Texas.

animal.description:
IMPORTANT!!!   All adoptions are by appointment only going forward and are spaced 30 minutes apart. PLEASE call the shelter directly during business hours for more information (see number below).  You need to make sure that the animal in which you have an interest is still available and to set up an appointment to meet the specific animal.  Once you arrive at the shelter for your scheduled appointment, please follow the directions that you were given over the telephone. If you are running late for your appointment or will be unable to make your scheduled appointment time, notify staff immediately. This will enable them to schedule that time for another prospective adoptive family. If necessary, they will be able to reschedule your appointment to a more convenient time.  

MERLE HAGGARD - Hey, y’all, here is another sweetheart in spite of the rough looking face he presents and his initial photos taken inside the building. He is actually a friendly, nice looking boy and his tail wags the whole time he is being photographed. His coloring is blue merle with white markings and he is a large boy with an intake weight of 82 pounds. Yikes! That is a whole lot of dog food each week. He is only about two years old, so that will be a whole lot of years of feeding this great big boy for some lucky person or family. MERLE has not been neutered and that still needs to be done before you can take him home. Please read the important information below and then call to schedule your adoption appointment.

Adoption fees are $80 for dogs.  Cat adoption fees are $50. Cash or check only. Please be sure to take the exact amount with you.

NOTE: All shelter fees are under review and may be changed or modified at any time without advance notice.

The shelter routinely vaccinates all healthy appearing animals upon their arrival at the shelter and deworms them.  Any animals not already spayed/neutered must have the procedure done through the veterinary clinic that contracts with the county before that animal can be released from the clinic to the new family. By state law, animals old enough to be given a rabies vaccine, must have that vaccine done, as well.  The vaccine is given by the veterinary clinic staff at a separate cost to the adoptive family. 

Hold periods for every incoming animal vary for several reasons including, but not limited to, whether the animal came in from the Cumberland County area, or from the City of Crossville, which contracts with the county for its animal shelter services.  Check with the staff to verify the availability date of every animal for which you have an interest.

For more information on this pet, call the shelter at (931)484-8525. The shelter is open Monday, Tuesday, Thursday, Friday, and Saturday from 10am to 2pm. Closed Wednesday and Sunday and county observed holidays.

animal.description: You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.Landry (TX) is a male Australian Shepherd/Great Pyrenees mix rescued in Texas. Our veterinary partner estimates that Landry is 4 weeks old at the time of intake in January 2021. Landry is good with people of all ages and other dogs. Landry's very short life thus far has been one of sadness and cruelty. Landry's Momma was hit by a car and left to die on the side of the road as the person who hit her just kept driving. To compound that sadness, Landry and his siblings, just 3 weeks old, were found clinging to their Momma's body. Landry and his siblings were picked up by Animal Control, and as they were too young to survive on their own, they typically would have been immediately euthanized. But fortune was shining down on Landry that day, as that particular Animal Control Officer diverted Landry into rescue, and now he will go on to live a happy life in a loving forever home. If you would like this cutie to become a member of your family, please apply online to adopt Landry (TX) at www.rescuedogsrocknyc.org.
